title: potato tot casserole
directions: Put meat firmly in baking dish.
Pour soup over evenly.
Put chopped onion and Tater Tots on top and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: frozen passion
directions: Pour the condensed milk and soda pop into ice cream freezer. Let it do the rest.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: oriental stew
directions: Cook meat in heavy pan and stir until browned.
Add beef broth and cook about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Steam broccoli, celery and carrots until slightly crunchy.
Dice green onions and add garlic. When meat is tender, add vegetables.
Sprinkle with soy sauce. Serve with fried rice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon together. Add carrots. Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and oil. Mix until combined. Add 1/2 cup of nuts and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until well done. Let cool until frosting is ready.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt 2 pounds Velveeta.
Add catsup, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Add sausage. Spread on party rye bread.
Freeze on 3 or 4 cookie sheets. Remove and stack in plastic bag.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 100.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add syrup, butter and salt.
Warm until butter melts.
Beat eggs and vanilla.
Stir in sugar; mix.
Pour in pie shell and spread nuts on top.
Bake on lower rack at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni chicken casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 of the cheese and remaining ingredients together.
Put into a 2 qt. greased casserole and sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Thaw bread dough at room temperature.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl.
In a second bowl, melt butter in microwave.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Use a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt the oleo in the pan and spread the crumbs over the bottom of the pan. Add the other items in order given and spread the milk over the top. Do not stir as it should be in layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut.
It's quick and easy for unexpected company.
It's also very rich and good!

title: teriyaki meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Shape into meatballs about 1 inch in diameter.
Heat oil in skillet.
Brown meatballs, remove from skillet.
Pour off drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook in skillet on low heat until sauce thickens, stirring constantly.
Return meatballs to skillet and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serve from electric skillet with small toothpicks.

title: thousand island dressing(for green or vegetable salads)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Thin with whipping cream, if desired.
Makes 3/4 cup of dressing.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: granny's pimento cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together in top of double boiler.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: peter money's dandelion treats
directions: Use young leaves, rinsed clean, as filling, tossed with other fresh greens with favorite dressing.

title: courier-journal oatmeal cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Spread on the still warm cake.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Cut up frying chicken into serving pieces.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Add rice over chicken, onion soup mix, chicken soup and mushroom soup.
Mix with water.
Put over all. Sprinkle paprika over all.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove cover and cook 15 minutes more.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk, then coat with cheese mixture.
Place in a baking dish.
Pour margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cake #1
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup flour to dredge fruit. Cream oil, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients, then fold floured fruits and nuts into mixture. Bake in tube pan or four 4 x 7 loaf pans at 325° for 1 or 1 1/2 hours.

title: greggie's favorite dessert
directions: In a 9 X 13 inch baking pan, place pineapple pie filling in the bottom.
Add cake mix evenly over the pie filling.
Add the nuts and chips and press slightly into cake mix.
Drizzle the butter evenly over the mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325 degrees for one hour.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Saut until tender the butter, zucchini and onion. Add cheese. Cook until cheese melts.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit 'n cheese kabobs
directions: Cut cheese into chunks or slices. Alternately, thread cheese and fruit onto wooden skewers. Serve immediately. Yield: About 3 dozen.

title: low-fat gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cilantro, in medium bowl. Cover bowl; chill between 2 hours (minimum) to overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve very cold:
(a) as a soup with chopped cilantro as a garnish, or (b) as a beverage or light lunch.
Put all ingredients in a blender until liquid.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until mixed well.
Beat eggs.
Mix chocolate well.
Mix flour then put in nuts.
It's now ready to bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Make frosting.

title: grandma cole's chicken cutlets
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in pan and press down.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Cut in slices, dip in egg and cracker crumbs and fry to light brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pistachio dream
directions: Spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Use other half of cool whip on top.
Spread evenly.
Refrigerate.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole. Bake at 350° until solid on top (approximately 45 minutes).

title: fried squash blossoms
directions: *Additional oil is needed for frying.

title: potato salad
directions: Beat egg, sugar, yellow mustard, vinegar and milk together. Heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over diced potatoes.
Add 1 to 4 tablespoons mayonnaise, pickle relish, onion, green pepper, olives, celery seed, salt and pepper.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix crackers and oleo; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save a few crumbs for the top.
Mix puddings with milk and combine with soft ice cream; spread over crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with the remaining crumbs and crushed candy bar.
Refrigerate.

title: quick dessert
directions: This dessert can be made in a large dish or individual dessert bowls.
Crumble Oreo cookies in the bottom of the dish.
Drizzle caramel topping over the cookies.
Spread a layer of ice cream over the cookies.
Top with a layer of Cool Whip.
Store covered in the freezer until ready to serve.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and milk.
Cook in saucepan on medium heat until thick.
Add coconut. Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: buttermilk cheese biscuits
directions: Mix soda with flour.
Make a well in the flour and pour oil and buttermilk in; stir quickly with a spoon until well mixed.	Add cheese and mix well.
Dough will be sticky.
Drop a spoonful at a time in flour and gently shape into a ball.
Place biscuits in a well-greased pan.
Brush the top with oil, bake at 450 degrees for 20 minutes or until brown.	Yields 18 biscuits.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and knead into a dough.
Roll out and cut into shape.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: magnolia house chicken breasts
directions: Brown
the
chicken
breasts in butter over medium-high heat for
minutes.
Sprinkle
with salt and pepper.
While chicken cooks, marinate sliced mushrooms in lemon juice.
Add the
Madeira or sherry to the chicken in the pan;
turn over. Simmer
another 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. (Do not overcook.) Remove to warm platter.

title: apple-pie-in-a-scoop
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar and flour.
Stir in milk. Cook and stir until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Stir in 1 cup of hot mixture into eggs.
Return all to saucepan.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Cover and chill.
Stir the whipping cream, pie filling, vanilla and cinnamon into the chilled mixture.
Freeze in a 4 to 5-quart ice cream freezer.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Mix melted butter with garlic powder and dry parsley.
Brush on hot biscuits.

title: crispy georgia salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour
into
glass dish to congeal. Serves 6.	Very good!

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, Karo, butter, salt and vanilla. Pour in unbaked pie shell (deep-dish).
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: crabmeat supreme
directions: Mix green pepper, pimentos, mustard, salt, white pepper, eggs and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Fold in crabmeat.
Makes 8 shells. Brush top with mayonnaise and paprika mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Layer macaroni and cheese; pour eggs and milk mix over crumbled crackers.
Cook at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's lime icing
directions: Cream together butter, salt and vanilla.
Add egg white, unbeaten and sugar.
Blend with lime juice and grated rind.
Beat well.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix meat, milk, bread and garlic salt.
Place in 9-inch pie pan.
Pat firmly.
Put sauce over mixture.
Drain mushrooms and arrange on sauce.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion in greased baking dish. Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Mix mushroom soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: mother's speedy rolls
directions: Place lukewarm water in mixing bowl with the sugar and yeast. Add salt and 2 cups of flour. Beat for 2 minutes. Add eggs and melted shortening. Beat for 1 minute. Gradually add 4 1/2 cups flour, stirring until dough is formed.

title: petros
directions: Take a bag of corn chips, turn it sideways and trim off edge to form a lengthwise pouch.
Spoon hot chili onto corn chips. Place remaining ingredients on chili and top with sour cream.
Eat out of the bag with a spoon.

title: sichuan chicken and pasta
directions: Spray 12 inch nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray; heat over medium high heat.
Cook chicken and onion in skillet 3 to 5 minutes or until chicken is light brown.
Stir in water; heat to boiling.
Stir in pasta.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until pasta is almost tender (do not drain).
Stir in packet of sauce mix from stir-fry mix until well blended.
Stir in vegetables.
Cover and cook 8 to 9 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Sprinkle with peanuts from stir-fry mix.
(I leave off the peanuts.)

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add melted cheese, dressing mix and Ro-Tel.
Mix together and serve.

title: asparagus-pea casserole
directions: Place asparagus in a deep, greased casserole.
Add cheese, eggs, peas and mushroom soup.
Sprinkle potato chips generously over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix cheese and sausage.
Pour in Bisquick. Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.
This makes a lot!!

title: frangelico biscotti(good for dunking!)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients (except nuts) in a large bowl.
Mix the eggs and liquids in another bowl.
Add liquids to dry ingredients gradually until dough is stiff.
Stir in nuts and mix well.
Shape into 2 logs.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: In 9 x 12-inch baking pan layer luncheon meat then chicken. Place bacon over chicken.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together and spread over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 275° for 3 hours.

title: homemade white cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together vegetable oil, vanilla, milk and eggs.
Then add sugar, baking powder, salt and flour.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Good high altitude recipe.

title: carrot and potato meat loaf
directions: Brown pork steaks with garlic and red pepper in oil in large frying pan. Pour off drippings.
Sprinkle salt over both sides of pork. Add water, cover tightly and cook slowly 30 minutes. Combine soy sauce, cornstarch, catsup and vinegar. Add with carrots and onion to pork.
Increase heat to medium-low and continue cooking, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until pork and vegetables are tender. Makes 4 servings.
359 calories per serving.

title: holiday cake
directions: Mix.
Put in 12 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Simple and delicious.

title: kayte beth's favorite cookie
directions: Examine cookie from all angles to make sure that there is filling inside.
Pull apart cookie.
With your teeth, scrape off all the filling.
Set cookie part aside or give it to your dog and ask mom for another one.

title: butter toffee
directions: Put butter, sugar, salt and water in a heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Cook to light crack stage or 285° on candy thermometer.
Add 1/4 cup nuts.
Pour out on well buttered jelly roll pan. While still hot, lay the Hershey bars on it.
When they are melted, spread out evenly and sprinkle on rest of nuts.
When cooled, break in pieces.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix beans with taco seasoning; spread on tray.
Mash avocados with lemon juice and sour cream.
Layer in order.
Serve with corn chips, Doritos, tortillas or any kind of corn chips.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Butter one side of bread thinly.
Cut in squares; put in bottom of bake dish.
Pour pineapple over bread.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and butter; pour over pineapple.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes, until top is nicely brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine broth, 1 cup water, carrots and potatoes in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer over low heat 10 minutes.

title: blackening season
directions: Mix seasonings together.
Sprinkle over chicken or other meats when grilling.

title: ruby bates' mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in a large iron skillet.
You may pour half of mixture into a medium size iron skillet and save the remaining mixture for next day, refrigerated. Bake in preheated oven at 350° until brown.

title: home ec.  punch
directions: Mix together undiluted juice, 7-Up and ginger ale in small punch bowl.

title: swedish sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes thin, crisp cookies.

title: salmon salad supreme
directions: Break salmon in bite size pieces.
Put in bowl.
Add celery and drained peas.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour over salmon mixture.
Toss lightly with fork.
Chill several hours.
Serve in lettuce cups.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Cut pineapple into smaller pieces.
Add strawberries, Eagle Brand milk and nuts; mix.
Then mix in Cool Whip.
Put in a long dish.
Chill.

title: mad cioppino
directions: In large pot (medium heat) in olive oil, cook onion, green pepper and garlic until tender (5 minutes).
Add tomatoes, wine, parsley, salt, basil, pepper and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling. Reduce to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Increase to medium heat.
Add clams; cook 10 minutes (stirring occasionally).
Add crab, shrimp, scallops and fish.
Cook 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink and scallop loses transparency.
Serve with hot French bread.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Insert cloves about 1/2-inch apart into orange.
Place in shallow baking pan; bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pierce orange in several places with 2-pronged fork.

title: tofu roast
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in sprayed 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Heat oil; saute onions and garlic; add beef.
Sear thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, over low heat 1 hour, uncovered 1/2 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and serve immediately.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let it stand overnight.
Hollow out unsliced loaf of rye bread.
Put dip into bread.
Cube the hollowed out bread and use with the dip.
Put the dip in bread when ready to serve.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Mix milk, eggs, salt and pepper together. Crumble fried bacon in the bottom of a pie shell. Sprinkle on all of cheese. Pour milk mixture over this. Bake 15 minutes at 450°. Reduce heat to 300° for 30 minutes more, until puffed and brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease pan with butter.
Use spring-form pan.
Dust pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Beat the cottage cheese until creamy. Gradually add cream cheese at high speed until it is well blended and creamy.
Gradually add sugar and eggs.
Reduce speed to low and add cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla.
Melt margarine; add sour cream and blend until creamy.
Pour mix into a prepared pan.
Heat oven to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Leave cheese cake in oven to cool for 2 hours.
Remove from oven; cool until chilled. Place in refrigerator before serving.
Can be frozen.

title: pork and potato scallop
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown pork chops in greased skillet. Prepare potatoes.
Blend soup, salt, pepper and celery seed. Arrange a layer of potatoes and onion in greased 2-quart baking dish, then cover with a portion of sauce.
Repeat layers until all are used, ending with sauce.
Place chops on top; sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour or until meat and potatoes are tender.

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking powder which has been sifted together; add the butter and crumb well with the fingers.
Take out 1 cup of crumbs (reserve for topping) and to the remaining, add the well beaten egg yolks and milk.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg white.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into well-greased deep pans and sprinkle top with the reserved crumbs.
Bake in a hot oven.
Bake them at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine
all ingredients and allow to set a few minutes.
Shape
into	walnut	size
balls. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake
at
for about 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, mayonnaise, cheese, egg, onion, butter and Ritz crackers together.
Spread into Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Top with 2/3 crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a casserole dish and top with crushed Ritz crackers and dribble melted butter over the crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
In a small bowl, mix nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon half of batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half of topping.
Add rest of batter and sprinkle with the rest of the topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab au gratin
directions: Melt butter in medium skillet.
Saute vegetables and garlic until tender.
To make cream and sauce; add flour and milk; cook to proper consistency.
Add whipping cream.
Add chopped, sauteed vegetables to cream sauce with dash of paprika.
Add Cheez Whiz and pimentos.
Stir in lump crabmeat.
Taste for proper seasoning. Pour in a round casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: venison steak and gravy
directions: Cut rabbit in pieces and roll in flour that has been seasoned with salt and some pepper.
Let stand while you cook onion in margarine.
When onion is wilted, add rabbit and brown on all sides.
Pour chicken or rabbit stock in the pan; add paprika and cook.
Simmer until the rabbit is tender.
Remove to a dish and keep warm.
Bring sauce in the pan to a boil.
Stir in sour cream. Add salt if necessary and lemon juice.
Heat, but don't boil, and pour over the rabbit.
Serve with rice or noodles, to 6.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook the potato; mash fine.
Add milk and oleo, then powdered sugar.
Roll out thin; spread with desired amount of peanut butter.
Roll up; cut into slices.
Store in a cool place.
Makes 80 pieces.

title: antipasto
directions: Wash, drain and dry lettuce.
Arrange leaves on a large platter.
Toss tomatoes in the Italian dressing.
Place on lettuce leaves.
Drain tuna; break into chunks and put on lettuce with the tomatoes.
Drain artichoke hearts and toss lightly in the dressing.
Arrange artichoke hearts, salami, Prosciutto, anchovy fillets, radishes, olives, pepper, celery on the platter. Sprinkle with parsley, capers and Italian dressing.

title: chicken divan
directions: Lay broccoli in a 9 x 12-inch greased baking dish.
Cut chicken into serving size pieces and place on top of the broccoli. Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle the top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: lemon "coffee bar" cake
directions: Dissolve jello in
hot water;
cool.
Mix together cake mix, oil, lemon	extract and eggs; add jello mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: never-fail toast 'n cheese souffle
directions: Remove crusts of bread.
Cut slices in half diagonally.
Place crusts from bread in bottom of well buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with 1/2 of the cheese.
Arrange bread triangles, overlapping, around edge of casserole, point sides up, saving 5 slices to place in center.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cheese, and pour over bread.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and let stand at least 1 hour.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat hash browns, chicken soup, milk and butter.
Remove from heat; add onions, cheese and sour cream.
Put into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with cornflakes and drizzle with extra butter. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Bake cake per directions in two round cake pans. Let it cool. Soften cream cheese to room temperature.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sherbet in chunks and oranges.
Stir.
Pour in 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix the first eight ingredients and place in casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight.

title: ham loaf(heritage recipe)
directions: Grind ham and pork. Add other ingredients. Mix and bake 35 minutes in greased pan.

title: bun candy
directions: In a double boiler melt the chips and peanut butter.
Spread half of mixture in a 9 X 13-inch pan.
Chill in freezer until firm.

title: orange glazed ham
directions: Bake ham for 1 hour at 325°.
Mix ingredients in a small bowl. Pour 1/3 of mixture over top of ham.
Cover ham with foil tent. Bake 1 hour.
Remove foil.
Spread more glaze over ham and bake for 15 minutes.
Serve with remaining warm sauce on the side. Serves 32 to 40.

title: vinegar pie(heritage recipe)
directions: Beat together yolks, sugar, and flour.
Add vinegar and water. Cook until thick, top with meringue and brown lightly.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together and spread over top.
Bake 5 minutes longer at 475°.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Make cornbread as usual.
Crumble cornbread and mix all ingredients together (all but 2 ounces of bacon bits and 2 ounces of cheese).
Put the other bacon bits and cheese on top.

title: 125 year old black walnut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease tube pan.
Cream together butter and shortening.
Mix with sugar well.
Add one egg at a time. Add flavoring.

title: pecan turtle squares
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter with a mixer for 2 to 3 minutes, until fine particles are formed.
(You will want to let the butter soften first.)
Press this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased) and pat it down firm.
Sprinkle pecans over this.
Now make a caramel with 2/3 cup butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Put this in a pan at
the same time and cook at medium heat, stirring constantly, until the surface begins to boil.
Cook 1/2 to 1 minute longer.
Pour over pecans.
Put bars in 350° preheated oven and bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
When you take it out of the oven, sprinkle the chocolate chips over.
When melted, spread them.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and flake salmon, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid. Combine all other ingredients.
Place in well-greased baking pan, or shape into loaf on greased baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: walnut squares
directions: Pour this on top of crust and bake 20 minutes or more.

title: jello and angel cake
directions: Prepare angel food cake mix according to package directions. Before putting cake into pan, take out 1 cup of mix and combine with 1 package of jello.
Fold into cake batter and pour into tube pan.
Bake according to package directions.

title: rum cheese cake
directions: Combine
crumbs,
cup
sugar and butter; reserve 3 tablespoons
crumb
mixture.
Press remaining crumbs in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
Meanwhile, combine gelatin and 1/2
cup
sugar
in
saucepan.
Stir in rum, lime peel and juice. Beat
egg yolks and blend into rum mixture.
Cook over medium heat,
stirring
constantly
until slightly thickened, about 8 minutes.
Remove
from
heat.
Beat
in
cream cheese until smooth.
Beat egg whites until foamy;
gradually beat in remaining 1/2
cup
sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Whip cream to soft peaks.
Fold egg whites into rum mixture.
Turn into
crumb lined pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: debbie's pizza bread
directions: With mixer, blend all ingredients together until smooth. Spread on baguette slices.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until warm.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix
all
together.
Put
in square or rectangular container. Freeze
for 24 hours or more.
When ready to use, cut and serve on
lettuce.
If
desired,
garnish
with
a bit of whipped cream or Cool Whip and a whole sweetened strawberry.

title: broccoli and lima bean casserole
directions: Cook and drain lima beans and broccoli; set aside.
Mix soup, water chestnuts, sour cream and onion soup.
Mix soup mixture with vegetables; put in casserole dish.

title: cheese soup
directions: Simmer vegetables and bouillon cubes in water until tender. Add Velveeta cheese and cream of chicken soup.
Do not let soup boil.

title: barbecue sausage links
directions: Put barbecue sauce into crock-pot; add jelly and stir until the two are mixed well.
Add sausage links.
Cook slowly for 3 to 4 hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound steak on both sides with mallet.
Cut in 4 pieces and set aside.
Place butter in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook on High for 2 minutes; add cornstarch and stir until well blended.
Stir in tomatoes, broth, onion, Worcestershire and seasoning.
Add steak; spoon sauce over steak.
Cover with lid.
Cook on High 35 minutes. Rearrange meat.
Arrange cherry tomatoes, beans and onion on top. Cover and cook on High 20 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Cover the cabbage and onion with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bring to boil the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the cabbage mixture.
Let stand at least 4 hours before serving.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.

Place all ingredients except cherries and corn flakes into mixing bowl and mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoonfuls into crushed corn flakes and roll into balls. Place on greased cookie sheet and press cherry into center.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes (time varies with different ranges).
Makes 5 dozen.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls and flatten with fork.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet at 325° for 10 minutes, until browned.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: plum dumplings
directions: Wash plums and split open just enough to remove seeds.
Fill cavity of each plum with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let stand while preparing dough.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add mashed potatoes and eggs.
Mix and knead to a soft dough.
Divide in 2 pieces.
Roll each on floured board slightly thicker than pie dough.
Cut with 3-inch round cookie cutter or floured glass. Place a plum in center of each and seal carefully.
Lower gently into boiling, salted water in 6-quart heavy pot.
When all dumplings are in, boil 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
When done, drain in a colander and rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Melt a little butter in a large skillet.
Add dumplings and brown slowly 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with sprinkled bread crumbs over top.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Place each breast half between two pieces of heavy-duty plastic wrap or waxed paper and set on a sturdy surface.
With flat side of meat mallet, pound to 1/4-inch thickness.
Remove plastic or waxed paper; dredge each piece slightly in flour.
In skillet, melt butter and oil.
Saute mushrooms over medium heat until tender.
With slotted spoon, remove from skillet.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook egg slowly in margarine in large skillet.
Stir in scallions and rice until lightly browned.
Add broth; bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1 cup mayonnaise. Put in baking dish. Crumble 2 tubes Ritz crackers and mix with 2 sticks margarine that has been melted. Sprinkle top. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: taco pizza
directions: In a saucepan, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain fat.
Stir in taco seasoning and water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes; set aside. Place crusts on ungreased pizza pans or baking sheets.
Combine beans and salsa; spread over crusts.
Top with beef mixture, chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with tomatoes and lettuce.
Makes 2 pizzas (6 to 8 servings each).

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift all other dry ingredients and add alternately with coffee; mix well.
Add apples, nuts and dates last.
Bake in 1 (9 x 3-inch) loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy brownies
directions: Beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts.
Pour in greased and floured 10 1/2 X 15 1/2 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes. Do not over bake.

title: cobbler
directions: This recipe works with any fruit.
Chop or slice large pieces.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry with paper towel.
Beat eggs with water and dip chicken in egg; drain.
Place chicken into bag and shake until well coated.
Place in baking dish.
Bake 60 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Cook 30 minutes on each side.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Bring tomato juice to boil in a small saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin, stirring 2 minutes or until gelatin dissolves. Cover and chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white. Stir in water, celery and onion.
Pour mixture into a lightly oiled 3 cup mold; cover with aluminum and chill until firm. Unmold onto a plate lined with lettuce.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Combine flour and Worcestershire sauce in Dutch oven; add water.
Cook and stir until thickened over medium flame.
Add onion, green pepper, mushrooms, seasonings, tomato sauce, tomatoes and soup.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook until done, approximately 5 minutes.
Serve immediately over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Beat together the first four ingredients for two minutes. Divide in three 8 or 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While cake is cooling, mix pineapple with juice and instant pudding together, then fold the Cool Whip into mixture. Spread between layers and on top of cake.
Must be refrigerated or can be frozen.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Brown chicken with butter.
Add cream of chicken soup, chicken and rice soup and cup of rice.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: curried cream of fruit soup
directions: Chop celery and apple and slice the banana.
In a saucepan, combine the onion, celery, banana, apple, potato and broth and simmer the mixture, stirring occasionally, for 25 minutes or until the potato is tender.
In a blender, puree the mixture with the curry powder and the pepper.
Return the mixture to the pan and stir in the cream.
Heat the soup over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally, until it is hot, but do not let it boil.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: *Chili beans are kidney beans in chili sauce.
If substituting kidney beans, increase the chili powder to 3 teaspoons.

title: last minute casserole
directions: Brown meat; salt and pepper.
Drain fat off meat and add onions.
Mix and add all other ingredients.
Toss.
Pour into a large 2 1/2 or 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lazy days meal
directions: Peel and slice vegetables.
Leave soaking in water until ready to use.
Tenderize round steak and cut into 4 pieces.
Sear on both sides in very hot skillet to seal in juices.
Place steak on a large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Salt and pepper if desired.
Arrange potatoes, onions and carrots on top of steak. Salt and pepper; dot with butter.
Close foil and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325 degrees for 20 minutes.
Put bacon on top when cooking.

title: parsley and parmesan baked chicken
directions: Pour salad dressing into 9 x 13-inch baking dish; add chicken, turning to coat on all sides.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Occasionally tilting dish and spooning dressing over chicken.
Drain, reserving dressing.
Combine egg and water.
In a plastic bag, combine cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, paprika and pepper.
Dip chicken into egg mixture, then shake a few pieces at a time, in crumb mixture to coat.
Return coated chicken to baking dish; spoon reserved dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: double brownie torte
directions: Heat butter and corn syrup; stir in chocolate chips.
Add eggs.
Stir in vanilla, flour and nuts.
Pour batter into 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients until thick, mashing berries against side of pan until it thickens.

title: salsa verde with tomato
directions: Mix together and serve with chips or toasted garlic bread. The longer this sits, the hotter it gets!

title: peter's potatoes
directions: Slice unpeeled
potatoes
1/8-inch thick.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 3-quart baking dish.
Layer sliced potatoes in baking dish;
season
with
salt
and pepper.
In saucepan, combine the cream,
mustard,
garlic and butter; heat to boiling. Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Uncover and top with cheese. Bake
for 30 minutes more, until potatoes are fork-tender. Makes 8 servings, about 295 calories each.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use one heaping tablespoonful per 1 cup hot water.

title: hawaiian cake ii
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Bake in 15 x 11-inch cookie sheet with edges at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine pudding with cold milk and cream cheese.
Fold in frozen topping.
Spread mixture on cold cake.
Drain pineapple very well.
In layers, put on fruit and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: bailey's irish cream mousse
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan and heat slowly until sugar is completely dissolved (mix should be boiling).
Place chocolate pieces, eggs and salt in blender container.
Turn blender to slowest speed and add hot syrup in a steady slow stream.
Blend until smooth.
Add Bailey's and Frangelico and mix well.
Fold this mixture into the whipped cream (it will be runny).
Transfer to a serving bowl or individual serving dishes. Chill at least several hours.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts or 20 servings.

title: corn custard
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, then add remainder of ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Insert knife in center; if it comes out clean, you are ready to eat!

title: fruity gelatin delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in medium bowl.
Add ice cubes to bowl.
Stir for 3 minutes or until melted.
Chill gelatin in refrigerator 15 minutes.
Fold in apple, grapes, banana and pecans.
Cover and chill for about 15 minutes.
Spoon about 1/4 of gelatin mixture into glass bowl.
Alternate layers of whipped topping, blueberries and remaining gelatin in bowl, ending with whipped topping.
Serve immediately.
Perfect served with angel food cake.
Instead of fresh fruit, canned fruit cocktail is a good alternative.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly and pack in pan.
Drizzle with pineapple juice and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in slow oven at 350°.

title: cattle clatter hash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and all seasonings to taste (approximately 1 teaspoon of garlic salt, 2 tablespoons of Worcestershire and 1 tablespoon of chili powder). Simmer.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder into bowl.
Add oil, eggs, salt, orange juice and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and set aside. Peel and slice apples.
Coat with cinnamon and sugar.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Alternate batter and apples, beginning and ending with the batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: stir-fry chicken and vegetables
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Add chicken pieces, tossing well.
To coat, let stand 1 hour.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Saute chicken in oil until lightly browned.
Add soy sauce and carrots, stirring well. Cook an additional 2 minutes, stirring well.
Add green onions, garlic and peppers.
Stir an additional 2 to 3 minutes.
Add zucchini, mushrooms and almonds.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Yield: 5 servings.
Contains 299 calories per serving.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add boiling water if too dry.
Serves approximately 6.

title: chicken pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
Roll out and line a casserole dish with dough.
Melt butter.
Add flour and seasoning.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Add liquids and cook slowly until thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Pour mixture into pastry lined casserole dish.
Top with remaining pastry. Pinch edges together.
Cut some vents in top crust.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mama's macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine macaroni, 2/3 of the cheese, milk and egg.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish covered with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven (preheated) for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: decorative icing
directions: Beat all ingredients until creamy.
Use food coloring to decorate, if desired.
This icing is used for decorating special cakes such as birthday, etc.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Cook onions and green pepper in butter about 5 minutes.
Stir in pimentos and cornstarch.
Add milk and cook until thickened. Add potatoes.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Note:
Can be made and refrigerated. Bake before serving.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack in pint jars. Add the hot peppers and the garlic. Put a tsp. of the dill seed over the okra in the jars. Heat the vinegar, 1 Tbsp of dill seed and salt in a sauce pan. Pour hot mixture over okra and seal the jars.

title: grandma claudy's cherry sauce
directions: In a pan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Pour reserved cherry juice in measuring cup and add enough water to measure 2 cups. Gradually stir water into sugar mixture. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly for 5 minutes or until thickened. Cut cherries in half or quarters.
Add cherries once mixture has thickened. This can be made ahead and reheated just before serving. Makes about 4 cups.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar together.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Mix Jell-O, 2 cups of boiling water and frozen strawberries together.
Let it stand until it is thick and strawberries are thawed.
Then pour it over cream cheese mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: In a 5 quart cast iron dutch oven, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onions, celery, bell peppers, garlic and bay leaves. Saut 3 - 5 minutes or until veggies wilt.	Add half of the crawfish tails and tomato sauce and blend into mixture.
Spoon in flour to form a roux.
Slowly add stock or water.
Bring to low boil and reduce heat to simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. After 30 minutes, add remaining crawfish, sherry, green onions, parsley and thyme.	Cook additional 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Add Louisiana pepper sauce at your own peril.
Serves a bunch.

title: hot rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of water and add 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Cream shortening and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Add yeast mixture, 2 teaspoons of salt, 2 cups of lukewarm water and flour.
Put in refrigerator and pinch off as needed.
Let rise about 2 hours and bake approximately 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: nut balls
directions: Cream butter, add next 4 ingredients and work with fingers until well blended.
Pinch off bits and roll into balls.
Bake on lightly buttered cookie sheet for 10 minutes in a preheated oven at 375°, while hot roll cookies in confectioners sugar.

title: traditional polish cream cake
directions: Spray 2 (9-inch) round baking pans.
Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine flour, cornstarch, baking powder and salt.
In a medium bowl, using a wire whisk, stir sugar and milk until blended.
Add egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Do not beat egg whites first. Gradually add egg white mixture to flour mixture; stir until smooth.
Add pecans and coconut and blend well.
Pour into pans. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; mix with sugar.
Stir in milk.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Sweeten peaches to taste with additional sugar; pour over batter.

title: cabbage slaw dressing recipe
directions: Mix all together well.
Cook until thickens slightly.
Pour over shredded cabbage.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, jello and cornstarch.
Add water and cook 1 minute, after it boils.
Cool and pour over sliced strawberries in a cooked pie shell.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice medium thin.
Place in baking dish.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender. Combine flour and seasonings; blend into onion mixture. Stir in Worcestershire sauce and vinegar until smooth. Add tomatoes and okra, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add shrimp and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Stir in rice. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chinese style chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake chicken wings for 30 minutes.
In saucepan, mix soy sauce, sugar, whiskey and ginger.
Cook over medium heat until sugar melts.
Add garlic.
Cook for 10 minutes. Baste chicken.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: garden fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pizza crust according to package directions, using a 12-inch pizza pan.
Place Provolone cheese over prepared crust.
In a small bowl, combine Ricotta cheese and egg; carefully spread over Provolone.
Spoon tomatoes over cheese mixture; top with mushrooms and green peppers.

title: pasta with broccoli, sausage and tomatoes(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Over medium heat, cook sausage for 2 minutes in 2 tablespoons oil, remove sausage from pan. Add broccoli, garlic, tomatoes, salt, pepper and red pepper to same pan on medium heat 3 minutes, then add cooked sausage and wine. Cook another 3 minutes, scraping bottom of pan, stirring; add chicken stock and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, keeping lid ajar; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cream butter and sugar with electric mixer in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add one egg and beat well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour and salt until well blended.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture into prepared pan (dust fingers with flour for easier handling). Bake 15 minutes.

title: pineapple banana pudding
directions: Put eggs, milk, vanilla, sugar, flour and butter in blender. Blend for 1 minute.
Pour in iron skillet and cook over low heat until thick as desired.
Put a layer of wafers in bottom of dish, then a layer of sliced bananas and a little pineapple. Pour some pudding mixture over this.
Repeat until finished.
Top with wafers.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in apples.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix Mexican cornbread mix according to directions on the package.
Put onion, garlic powder and jalapeno relish in blender. Puree.
Add to cornbread mixture.
Then add cream-style corn and add cheese last.
Put oil in pan and heat in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat to 425°.
Add cornbread mixture to pan and bake for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter.
Add soda to sour cream and mix well.
Add to creamed mix.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mix. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until edges start to brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water and cook together until it forms a hard ball, 350° on candy thermometer.
Add peanuts and butter and cook in the syrup until it browns.
Add vanilla. Remove from heat and add soda.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered pans.
Spread thinly.
When cold break into pieces.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Mix just until incorporated.
Pour into well greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a bowl.
Cut in shortening with knives or pastry blender until evenly distributed.
Store in covered container.*
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Dice potatoes and boil 10 minutes.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a medium bowl, with an electric mixer set at medium speed, beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla until creamy.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Spread thickly over cake, making swirls with the knife.
Makes 2 1/2 cups of icing.

title: jalapeno black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add ground beef and brown.
Stir in peas, rice and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: coney island hot dog
directions: Place chili in glass bowl.
Heat.
Stir.
Put hot dog on open buns.
Put in oven till warm.
Spoon chili over and sprinkle with cheese.

title: dove in sauce
directions: Place doves in saucepan with tomato juice; cover and simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Remove doves; reserve liquid.
Place diced bacon and margarine in flame-proof casserole; heat until hot.
Add onions and saute until golden.
Add birds, garlic, thyme, bay leaf and mushrooms.
Stir to brown, then add tomato juice and cooking liquid.
Cover and simmer slowly until meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Remove birds to a warm serving platter.
Thicken sauce with flour.
Pour over doves and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend oil and sugars on low until well mixed. Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Stir together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in walnuts and carrots by hand. Pour batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or fluted pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan. Then top with powdered sugar or frosting of your choice.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Shake all ingredients together.
Place chicken in casserole dish and pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered, then uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Mix together oil and eggs; let stand a few minutes.
Add sugar to mixture, mixing by hand, and let stand 5 minutes longer.
Add 2 cups flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, apples and nuts.
Mix.
Then mix in remaining cup of flour.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Spray skillet.
Add eggs on low heat without stirring.
Let eggs set.
Break up with fork.
Remove and reserve.
Combine 2 onions and 2 tablespoons of soy sauce; cook and stir until onions are golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to a boil. Reduce and simmer for 1 minute.
Stir in egg.
Remove, cover and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: creamy orange pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; keep juice.
Add enough water to equal 1 cup. Heat to boiling.
Add jello and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth. Chill until jello has just started to set.

title: fruit and nut brie
directions: Cut a wedge out of the Brie equal to 1/4 of the wheel. Turn and stack this on top of the remaining 3/4 of the wheel. Pour about half the preserves into a small bowl and stir to loosen. Pour preserves over Brie, then sprinkle with pecans, bacon and raspberries. You may use whatever amount of each ingredient you would like, just make sure there is enough so everyone can get some of each with each bite.

title: deutsch chili sauce
directions: Peel and grind ingredients.
Add tomatoes and cook until thick from 4 to 6 hours.

title: old time gingerbread with warm lemon sauce
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving or early in the day, preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Into a large bowl, measure 1/2 cup boiling water and all the ingredients with mixer on low speed. Beat until well blended. Increase speed to high and beat 2 minutes. Pour batter into cake pan; bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool to serve later. Serve with Lemon Sauce.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Line half of tortillas on bottom overlapping.
Brown beef and onion.
Mix seasonings in meat.
Spread meat mixture over tortillas.
Pour beans over meat.
Put half of cheese over beans. Layer remaining tortillas over cheese.
Mix soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes together in blender; put over tortillas.
Top with remainder of cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove foil to brown cheese.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, garlic and 1/4 cup water; set aside.
In wok, stir-fry chicken in hot oil 2 minutes. Add veggies, stir-fry for 4 minutes.
Add soy sauce mixture, cook and stir until slightly thickened.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook pork roast in crock-pot overnight.
Remove meat from broth the next morning.
Place broth in separate bowl and refrigerate.
Tear meat in strips and remove fat.
When broth has completely cooled, skim fat from the top and pour remaining broth in with the meat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: creamy shrimp bisque
directions: In a 4-quart pot over medium-high heat, cook shrimp shells in hot olive oil until pink, constantly stirring with slotted spoon. Discard shells, leaving flavored oil in pot.
Add shrimp to oil and cook, over medium-high heat, stirring frequently, until shrimp turn pink, about 3 minutes; spoon into bowl.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add butter and chopped vegetables, cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining ingredients with the exception of the tomatoes and cream, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until rice is tender (about 15 minutes).
Remove pot from heat, discard bay leaf, drain juice from tomatoes, remove seeds from tomatoes, stir tomatoes into rice combo and add shrimp.
In blender at high speed, blend mixture, one half at a time, until smooth.
Return shrimp mixture to pot, stir in cream.
Bring to short of boiling, over medium heat.

title: banana ale
directions: Boil water and sugar together for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Mix oranges, bananas, lemons and pineapple juice in blender.
Mix sugar/water and fruit mixture together.
Set in freezer for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake per directions.
Bake approximately 30 minutes. Before cake is done, boil pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes. Spread over cake while both are hot.
Let cool completely.

title: divine divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a saucepan.
Place over low heat.
Boil until mixture forms threads when dropped from a spoon.
Slowly pour 1/2 the syrup into the egg whites, beating while pouring.

title: corn chowder(serves 6)
directions: Combine broth, ham, onion, carrot and potatoes. Add herbs. Cook until potatoes are done. Mash potatoes. Add corn and half and half. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in pimento.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Cook cake by directions on box in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
When done and still hot, punch holes all over the cake with a toothpick or fork.
Pour condensed milk over cake and spread.
Next pour cream of coconut over this.
When cake is cool enough, spread Cool Whip over this. Then sprinkle coconut over the Cool Whip.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together whipped cream and sour cream.
Spread on cake. Cut angel cake across the middle; hollow out the bottom part of cake.
Slice 1 quart of strawberries.
Sweeten.
Add the quart of strawberries to the hollow part of cake.
Add sour cream and whipped topping that is mixed together in the tunnel of the cake. Put the other top part of cake over bottom of cake.
Spread whipped topping and sour cream on cake.
Decorate cake with pint of strawberries.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Overlap potatoes in large baking dish. Scatter onion on top.
Pour butter over all potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake 1 hour until well browned.

title: delicious salad
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin; cool.
Add to other ingredients and chill.
Refrigerate, but don't freeze.
Serve on lettuce leaf. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and chipped beef
directions: Grease casserole dish well.
Layer bottom of dish with chipped beef.
Fold chicken breast and wrap with bacon.
Place side by side in dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, for at least 3 hours at 275°.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: 10 day slaw
directions: Chop these ingredients fine.

title: "the hulk" salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding well (do not drain).
Add pecans, marshmallows and cherries, mixing well.
Fold in whipped topping and chill overnight.

title: "tequenos" venezuelan appetizer
directions: Cut cheese into thin strips (approximately 1 1/2 inches long). (The amount of cheese strips will be the amount of tequenos you will have.)

title: popcorn cake
directions: Microwave the butter, oil and marshmallows until the marshmallows are puffy and the butter is melted.
Pour the mixture over the popped corn, candy and peanuts.
Stir well.
Place in a Tupperware tube pan.
Cool before turning out.

title: white chocolate salties
directions: Melt candy coating in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until candy coating melts. Remove from heat.
Cool 2 minutes.
Add pretzels and nuts.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill 20 minutes or until firm.

title: may morning strada
directions: Trim bread crusts and butter generously.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Put grated cheese over bread, then a layer of meat.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over all.
Put green chiles on top.
Bake for 50 minutes in 350° oven, uncovered.
You can mix this night before cooking and serving.
When done, cut into squares.
Good with fruit plate and muffins.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix and fill flour tortilla shells and roll.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with carton of sour cream and 1 cup grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening (or oil), beaten egg, sugar and salt to scalded milk.
Dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Add water and yeast mixture to the liquid milk mixture.
Sift and measure flour, adding liquid mixtures.
Mix well.
Cover with warm cloth and let stand 10 to 30 minutes.
Knead dough down, adding more flour, if needed.

Cover again and let rise 30 to 45 minutes. Knead dough down again, roll out and cut out rolls with cutter. Place in greased or Pam pan and let rise for 30 to 45 minutes. Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fudgies(no bake cookies)
directions: In a 2 quart sauce pan put first four ingredients, bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla and stir until smooth.
Stir in the Oatmeal.

title: quick and easy frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth and creamy consistency.

title: grilled chicken caesar salad
directions: Grill chicken.
Slice cooled chicken into strips and set aside.
Wash lettuce in cold water and dry thoroughly.
Combine anchovies, Egg Beaters, garlic, mustard, oil, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce in blender (set on "blend").
When mixture is whipped into a froth, toss on salad greens.
Add croutons, cheese and chicken.
When ready to serve, fresh mushrooms and 1/2 cup finely shredded red cabbage may be added for presentation.

title: sweet potatoes & apples
directions: Cook for 8 minutes, stir in 3 Tbsp. butter.

title: eggless custard
directions: Mix
pudding
as
directed on package.
Add sugar.
Mix well and add to milk.
Whip Dream Whip as directed on package, add to milk mixture with vanilla.
This can be made in mixer, blender or by hand.

title: sticky buns
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
On top of this sprinkle nuts and raisins.
Then cut up thawed bread dough into 1/2 inch slices and cover nuts and raisins.
Melt remaining ingredients and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
After boiling, remove from heat and pour over bread and nuts/raisins.
Cover immediately with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
Next morning bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven and turn upside down on serving dish.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Mix soup mix, beef bouillon and water together and pour over roast.
Cover and cook 12 hours at 250°.
When done so meat falls apart, remove bones and fat.
Serve on buns.

title: microwave some-mores
directions: Break graham cracker in half and place one-half on paper plate.
Top with chocolate bar and then the marshmallow.
Heat in microwave for 20 seconds, or until marshmallow and chocolate are melted.
Top with second half of graham cracker.

title: easy white cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add shortening and 1 cup milk; beat for 1 minute.
Scrape bowl.
Add eggs, remaining 1/2 cup milk and vanilla; beat for 1 minute, or until smooth.
Grease and flour 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat 3 egg yolks well.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well.
Add thawed lemonade and stir until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Make meringue with egg whites.
Add 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla to egg whites. Beat until it forms stiff peaks.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until well mixed.
Cook at 350° until brown.
When cooled, put in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Mix or sift all dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs, pumpkin and water.
Beat until smooth.
Fill each loaf pan 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday nuts
directions: Saute nuts in butter for 2 minutes.
Add soy sauce and remove from heat.
Sprinkle seasoning over nuts and let cool.
Store in airtight container (let nuts cool completely before tasting them or you will be disappointed!).

title: lemonade cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and set aside.
Beat eggs and oil well. Add cake mix and flavoring.
Beat well and add jello mixture.
Line bottom and sides of tube pan with waxed paper. Grease and flour well.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour.
While cake is baking, mix lemonade diluted with sugar.
When cake is done, run knife around edges to loosen from pan and pour lemonade over and down sides of cake.
Let cake stay in pan until cool.
For a nice large cake, double the recipe.
This is absolutely delicious.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Bring to a boil on medium heat. Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Mix well.
Add cereal.
Spread evenly in a buttered pan.
Melt chips together.
Spread over mixture and let cool.
Do not refrigerate.
Serves 15.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave until cheese melts.
Stir well.
Dip with Doritos or tortilla chips.

title: rum cake
directions: Beat cake mix, eggs, apricot nectar and oil for ten minutes. Pour into Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: double apple bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray muffin tins with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, mix together dry ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
In a medium bowl, beat egg whites until frothy. Stir in remaining ingredients, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spoon into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add carrots, nuts, salad oil and beaten eggs.
Bake in 2 layers or loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes for layers and 40 to 50 minutes for loaf.
Cool cake and frost.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan, cook the sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add quickly the peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: daffodil dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add eggs, onion, salt, pepper, garlic powder and parsley; mix well.
Serve with bread sticks, crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: chocolate peanut butter cups
directions: Place 1/2 the chips in a paper muffin cup.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Repeat for 30 seconds, or until chips are completely melted.
Place in freezer for 5 minutes.
Spoon peanut butter on top of chocolate, then sprinkle with remaining chips. Microwave on High for 1 minute; stir and swirl.
Repeat for 30 seconds, or until chips are completely melted.
Place in freezer for 5 minutes.
Remove and eat.
Makes 1 muffin cup so rich it can be shared.

title: clam casserole
directions: Mix all together, saving a few crackers for top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon layer cake
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add extracts.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until fluffy after each addition. Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with milk.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into patties.
Roll in corn meal and fry.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over melted butter and press down.
Sprinkle on coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips. Pour milk evenly over all.
Sprinkle on nuts. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack and cut into 1 x 2-inch bars. Makes 48 bars.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hazelnut pavlova with coffee cream
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Draw two 8-inch circles on a boil-lined baking sheet.
In a large mixing bowl, combine egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar.
Beat egg white mixture with an electric mixer on medium speed until soft peaks form (tips curl).
Gradually add 1 1/3 cups of the sugar, a tablespoon at a time, beating about 7 minutes on high speed until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight) and sugar is almost dissolved.
Gently fold in the 1 cup nuts.
Spread half of egg white mixture over each circle on baking sheet.
Bake 35 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Let meringues dry in oven, with door closed, 1 hour.

title: quick and easy rice jambalaya
directions: In large skillet heat sausage until lightly browned.
Add chicken, onion, pepper and celery.
Cook and stir until chicken is done.
Stir in tomatoes, okra, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir and serve.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix together butter or margarine, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup flour; press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute sliced zucchini and onion in olive oil for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except pasta.
Cook on medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes or until zucchini is cooked.
Stir in cooked pasta (pasta bows make this a pretty dish).
Let flavors mix for at least 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: To one beaten egg; add sugar, butter, mustard, celery seed, turmeric, salt and pepper.
Add vinegar and milk.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: vegetable trio
directions: Drain beans and peas; place in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients except onion rings.
Add to bean mixture; stir until mixed.
Place onion rings over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Bread crumbs may be used instead of onion rings.

title: corn and shrimp soup
directions: Make roux with oil and flour in heavy pot.
Add next 5 ingredients and seasonings.
Cook until tender.
Add shrimp and cook until pink; add tomatoes, both cans of corn and water.
Bring to a boil and add parsley.
Let simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend and beat sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in apples, bran and flour (sifted), baking soda, spices and salt.
Spread in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon cool("share the sunshine")
directions: Mix and press into a 14 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana julius
directions: Mix together in blender.
Add 6 ice cubes.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all the ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a well-greased or nonstick cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 30.

title: easy brownies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla and stir well.
Pour the batter into a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix together like for pie crust. Add about 1 cup milk to make soft dough. Scrape onto floured counter. Knead together slightly. Pat to desired thickness. Cut with pizza cutter. Place on baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: After browning meat and onion add dressing, seasoning, tomatoes with chilies, tomato sauce and cans of water, and simmer a few minutes.
Put in a large pot, and add, chicken broth, corn, beans, and hominy.
Heat to a boil and simmer for a little while, just to get the flavor mixed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oriental cashew crunch
directions: Mix together oil, soy sauce, garlic powder and onion powder. Pour over first 3 ingredients.
Stir quickly to blend.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Dice chicken and brown.
Layer cooked lasagna noodles, cottage cheese, diced chicken and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers 2 to 3 times.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Stir in cream of chicken, milk and mushrooms.
Pour over layers and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add shredded cheese on top and let melt.

title: potato casserole with corn flakes
directions: Melt butter. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into 2 quart casserole. Then melt 2 tablespoons butter; add 3/4 cup crushed corn flakes and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken fiesta
directions: Cook noodles following label instructions. Drain. Combine with onions and 1 can of the mushroom soup in a greased, shallow, 12-cup baking dish and sprinkle with peas. While noodles cook, pull skin from chicken breasts. Cut each in half. Arrange in a single layer over peas. Spread with the remaining can of soup. Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender and sauce is bubbly. Makes 8 servings.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add flavoring.
Fold into mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Finely chop all the fruit.
Pour sugar over fruit.
Let set for
2 hours.
Prepare jello, using only 1 1/2 cups water (or even
less) as juice forms from the fruit.	Combine jello and fruits and chill until set.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk with mixer until creamy.
Add pie filling, drained pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix together. Chill and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and mix with first 3 ingredients.
Melt Cheez Whiz and cream of chicken soup together and pour over rice mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh banana bundt cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add bananas, eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to first mixture and blend.
Add sour cream.
Beat until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; invert.

title: dolly corban's asparagus salad
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water; heat to boiling 1 cup water with sugar, vinegar and salt.
Add gelatin mixture to hot liquid and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients including asparagus juice.
Pour into bowl, chill until set.
Cut into squares.
Garnish; mayonnaise and lettuce if desired.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Rinse kidney beans and drain.
Put into small bowl.
Add chopped onion and celery.
Mix milk, vinegar, mayo and sugar until smooth.
Add slowly to beans, using just enough to coat beans. Chill and serve.
Serves approximately 4.

title: no homework swiss cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in medium mixing bowl.
Allow mixture to reach room temperature.
Serve with crackers.
Yield: approximately 3 cups.

title: penuche frosting
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar and milk; boil 2 minutes or less.
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm. Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Frost cake.

title: fish and shellfish stew
directions: Saute the mushrooms, onions and green pepper until the pepper is soft.
Add the tomatoes, tomato sauce and wine.
Bring to a simmer and add the garlic powder, spices and potatoes.
Simmer for about 25 minutes.
Add the fish chunks and cook about 5 minutes. Add crabmeat, oysters with liquor and shrimp; simmer another 5 minutes or until the shrimp have turned pink.
Serve sprinkled with chopped parsley.

title: preserving summer's bounty
directions: Puree.
Shape into small balls and freeze.
Treat your pasta, steak or chicken to fresh herb butter in winter.
Another butter treat to freeze is strawberry butter.
Mash strawberries into unsalted butter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and stir in stuffing.
Put 1/2 of mixture in buttered baking dish; spread over this chicken, cut in bite-size pieces.
Pour over the chicken 1 1/2 cups of reserved broth.
Mix sour cream and chicken soup and spread on chicken.
Add remainder of stuffing and spoon over with 6 to 7 tablespoons broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's jelly filled cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and brown sugar.
Add the egg yolk and flour.	Roll
dough
into
balls the size of walnuts. Dip in beaten
egg
white; roll in chopped nuts.
Press center of the ball with
finger
to
make a small well or depression. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Fill well with jelly or jam; bake 5 minutes more.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cut up and place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add peas and carrots to the chicken.
Add broth, chicken soup and top with mixture of milk, Bisquick and melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef louise
directions: Mix all ingredients (even raw meat) together.
Put in a covered casserole and bake at 325° for three hours.
Don't peek! Serve over rice or noodles.

title: veal scaloppine with tomatoes and olives(60 minute gourmet)
directions: Pound each piece of meat lightly between 2 sheets of plastic wrap with a flat mallet or the bottom of a heavy skillet. Sprinkle the meat on both sides with salt and pepper.
Beat the egg with the water in a shallow dish.
Coat the scaloppine on both sides with flour; dip them into the egg mixture until well coated on both sides.
Heat the oil and 1 tablespoon of the butter in a large skillet.
Add the piece of veal and cook over high heat about 1 minute.
Turn and cook on the other side for 1 minutes; as the pieces are cooked, transfer them to a warm platter and keep hot.
Wipe out the skillet.
To the clean skillet, add the remaining butter.
When it has melted, add the pepper strips, olives, garlic and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, tossing and stirring, until the peppers are crisp tender.
Add the tomatoes and cook about 1 minute.
Add the oregano and vinegar and stir well.
Cook over high heat about 30 seconds.
Pour the mixture over the veal and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hawaiian yams
directions: Cream potatoes and add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Ten minutes before taking out of oven, fix topping.

title: grandma's rhubarb dessert
directions: Take package of graham crackers, crushed fine and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rhubarb, water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until soft and thick.
Pour over crushed graham crackers, when lukewarm, add about 2 to 3 cups small marshmallows over top.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Prepare package of instant pudding and put on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for a few hours before serving.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cheese with cream in very large bowl.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Add fruits and nuts.
Fold in the sweetened whipped cream.
Pour into mold and freeze.

title: fruit tea
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Before serving, add three 12 ounce cans of cold 7-Up or Sprite to the mixture.
Stir and serve over ice.

title: heavenly banana cream pie
directions: Put mixing bowl in freezer (glass bowl).
In frosted bowl, mix pudding, 1 pint whipping cream and milk; beat until nice and thick. Use 1 1/2 bananas, sliced; layer in bottom of pie shell.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture on top of banana slices.
Layer with remaining 1 1/2 banana slices.
Pour remaining pudding mixture on top.
Beat remaining pint of whipping cream and pour on top.
Sprinkle crushed nuts on top.
Refrigerate until set.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in pumpkin.
In another bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture. Blend in nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Pour mixture into pans and bake for about 70 minutes at 350°.
Cool on wire rack.

title: polish apple pancakes
directions: In bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
In another bowl, lightly beat the egg; add milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Fold in apples.
Pour batter by 1/2 cupfuls onto a lightly greased hot griddle and spread to form a 5-inch circle (can be fried in frypan with melted butter).
Turn when bubbles form.
Cook the second side until golden brown. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.
Yields 14 to 16 pancakes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Set oven control at 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir nuts into flour mixture.
Set aside.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat to boiling point in saucepan the water and butter.
Stir in flour until mixture leaves the pan and forms a ball.
Cool. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beat until smooth and velvety.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes, until dry.
Allow to cool slowly.
Fill with whipped cream or custards.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together well.
Add the vanilla, salt, flour and baking soda.
Mix and add 1/2 cup more flour, if needed, until dough does not stick to your finger.
Stir in with spatula the chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 floured bread pans, 1/2 amount of batter in each pan.
In small bowl, mix 5 Tbsp. sugar, 4 tsp. cinnamon, and 1/3 cup ground nuts.
Sprinkle over batter in pans.
Pour remaining batter in each pan and bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs, shortening and buttermilk.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: plain cake(club member: john waters)
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and shortening well.
Add milk and flour; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour in cake pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, then add cornbread mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° until light brown for 25 minutes.

title: pork roast
directions: Make slits in roast with knife to a depth of approximately 3 inches deep every 5 to 6 inches.
In a small bowl, mix garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Dampen mixture with water.
Rub seasoning over roast.
Heat small amount of oil in deep heavy iron pot.
Brown roast well on all sides.
After browning, add water and cover.
Let cook on high heat for 5 minutes.
