Reduce heat and let simmer, turn occasionally.
Bake 4 hours or until well done. For additional flavor, stuff roast and keep in freezer for 3 to 4 days before baking.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix tomato soup, vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper, Crisco oil and sugar well.
Add carrots, onion and green pepper.

title: elegant cheesecake
directions: Combine ingredients and pat into the bottom and part way up the sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.

title: pannekocken - oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in an 8-inch pie pan.
Mix ingredients with wire whip.
Pour mixture into pie pan.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon. Bake 18 minutes (golden brown).
Serve with syrup or fruit pie filling (warm).

title: chicken tortilla
directions: Cut up chicken and season to taste; boil until done.
Remove chicken; let cool; debone.
Dip tortillas in the chicken broth to soften; line a 13x9 inch pan.
Place chicken on top of tortillas. In a bowl mix onion, bell pepper, soups, tomatoes, garlic salt, and chili powder.
Blend well, pour over chicken. Cook at 350 degrees for 30 minutes, put cheese on top; cook for additional 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: divine potatoes
directions: Set aside some of the cheese.
Mix all the remaining ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°. Sprinkle the remainder of cheese on top and put back in oven until melted.
Can be served as a main dish or side dish.

title: pancho's salsa
directions: Finely dice jalapenos, onion, cilantro and tomato.
In medium bowl mix all ingredients.

title: crab ball
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, garlic powder, salt and crab. Add chopped onion.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: lite punch bowl cake
directions: Bake angel food cake as directed on package.
Place half of cake in a large punch bowl.
Add half to the other ingredients, layering each as you go.
Add other half of cake and the rest of the ingredients in layers.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: heavenly hash or pink salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: two crust lemon pie
directions: Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water in a medium saucepan. Add boiling water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to boiling.
Boil 1 minute until thickened. Stir in sugar, lemon rind and butter.
Cool.
Stir in eggs and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into pie shell.

title: cathy's homemade bread
directions: Combine in large bowl the flour, sugar, salt and Crisco.
Mix with your hands until well blended.
In 1 quart of warm water, dissolve yeast and add to flour mixture.
Work up until stiff. Grease sides of bowl and top of bread.
Let dough rise to top of bowl.
Grease hands and work down.
Put into greased pans and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, peanut butter, eggs and milk in large bowl. Mix on low speed until blended. Stir in peanut butter pieces. Drop slightly rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes or until slightly browned. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheets. Remove to cooling rack. Yields 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour fruit cocktail over pie filling evenly.
Spread dry cake mix over fruit evenly.
Pour melted butter over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is slightly browned.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix butter, soup, onion, cheese and sour cream together.
Pour over potatoes, then top with corn flakes.
Drizzle with butter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bacon delight sandwiches
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Spread mayonnaise mixture on bread (and trim crust if desired).
Cut bread in fourths diagonally.

title: ground beef fajitas
directions: We cook this
in
the
winter
over
an open flame in a large disc blade
with
legs, but you can cook it in a skillet on the stove.
Brown ground beef until almost done; drain off fat.
Add margarine,
the
seasonings, onion and bell pepper. Cook, while stirring,
until vegetables are tender.
Add wine and let cook until wine has evaporated.
Assemble by placing a small amount
of the
meat
mixture and desired toppings on a flour tortilla, then roll up tortilla.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough, if not, just scrub and rinse. Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use handle of spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Place your potatoes in a baking pan and fan them out slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with chives.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Sprinkle on your cheese and bake for another 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: mama's baked beans
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bay country crab soup
directions: Put first 8 ingredients in large pan and simmer, covered, until meat is tender, about 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender.

title: goof balls
directions: Heat just to boiling the Karo syrup and sugar.
Take off heat and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Form into balls and let cool.

title: aunt pat's fruit salad
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and butter in top of double boiler or heavy saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until texture is custard-like. Remove from heat. Drain the canned fruit.
Mix with marshmallows.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Boil rice in chicken broth.
Boil broccoli.
Mix sour cream, chicken soup (undiluted), broccoli, chicken and rice.
Put in baking dish and top with Cheddar cheese; sprinkle with chili powder.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and apples.
Blend with electric mixer.
Pour in nuts and apples and mix.
Pour in long pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
About 5 minutes before done, pour 1 bag of butterscotch morsels on top.
Spread when warm and melted.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Roll out half of the dough at a time into 3/8-inch thickness.
Using a pizza cutter, cut to desired shapes and size.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 375°.
Turn off oven and leave the biscuits in oven until cool.
Yields about one pound.
If placed in an airtight container, biscuits will keep for weeks.

title: blue cheese mousse
directions: Sieve cheese into a bowl, then gradually beat in half the cream.
Place bowl over a pan of hot water, stirring until smooth. Allow to cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and sprinkle paprika on top and chill.

title: microwave chex party mix
directions: In small bowl, add Lawry's seasoned salt and Lea & Perrins Worcestershire sauce to melted margarine; mix well.
Pour Chex, nuts and Butter Buds into large Ziploc bag.
Pour margarine mixture into Ziploc bag; seal top of bag securely.
Shake bag until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour contents of bag into large, microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: granny's caramel pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour and 1 cup sugar.
Add milk.
Cook a few minutes and set aside.
Caramelize 1/2 cup sugar and add part of the cooked mixture to the caramelized sugar.
Mix well and then pour the remaining cooked mixture in.
Finish cooking until thick enough for pie filling.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff and add 3 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour on top of pie and bake at 325° until brown.

title: vacuum cleaner cookies
directions: Combine margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Stir together until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pat mixture into bottom of well-greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat remaining 2 eggs lightly, then beat in softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour over mixture in jelly roll pan, spreading evenly. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool pan on wire rack until room temperature.
Makes 4 dozen bars (48 servings).
Preparation time is 10 minutes, cooking time is 45 minutes.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken and remove bone.
Cook spaghetti, broken in small pieces, in chicken broth.
Saute onion in 1 stick of butter.
Cut Velveeta cheese in cubes.
Mix all ingredients together and cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Stir together the flour and cinnamon.
Mix together the sugar, oil, eggs, and carrots.
Add to first mixture.
Pour into pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: sunken treasure(mexican nacho chip dip)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into dish (large 8 x 8-inch glass).
Grate and sprinkle cheeses on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Use as a dip with nacho chips.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Wash eggplant; peel and slice.
Brown ground beef in skillet and drain well.
In shallow baking dish, spread small amount of spaghetti sauce mixture on bottom; alternate layer of eggplant then sauce, ending with sauce.
Last sprinkle Parmesan cheese on sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until eggplant is tender when pierced with fork.

title: salmon loaf with cheese
directions: Combine ingredients, using enough crumbs to make stiff mixture.
Put in a loaf pan.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: sloppy joes filling(quick and easy)
directions: In large frying pan, brown meat with onion.
Stir in salt, pepper and flour until well blended.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring frequently, 20 minutes or until thick.
Serve on split and toasted hamburger buns (or toasted bread).
Makes enough filling for 5 servings.

title: bump on a log cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat butter or margarine with electric mixer on medium speed until softened, about 30 seconds.
Add sugar, cocoa, egg and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy with mixer on low speed.
Beat in water.
Add flour gradually until well mixed.
If necessary, cover and chill 2 hours.

title: hip-padder bars
directions: Combine milk, 2 tablespoons butter and chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Cook, stirring until melted and smooth.
Set aside to cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix the flour, garlic salt, pepper and parsley flakes in a bag with meat to coat.
Brown meat in butter or margarine.
Add chicken broth and wine. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally and taste sauce. Add more garlic, if necessary. Add the mushrooms and parsley after 15 minutes.
Add the sour cream and mix in well.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: black forest crepes
directions: Prepare the whipped topping mix in a large bowl following package directions, using skim milk and vanilla.
Fold in yogurt until well blended.
Stir in the chopped black cherries.
Spoon a generous 1/4 cup cherry mixture onto center of crepe.
Spread to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Roll up crepe.
Repeat with remaining filling and crepes.
Refrigerate crepes for several hours to chill and firm filling.

title: double raspberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin, salt and jelly in boiling water.
Measure 1/2 cup and set aside.
Add frozen berries to remaining gelatin; stir until berries separate and mixture thickens.
Pour into 1-quart ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Blend reserved gelatin into sour cream; chill.
Unmold ring.
Beat cream mixture until smooth; serve in center of ring.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Place torn spinach or lettuce in a large bowl; add the sliced green onion.
Sprinkle a generous amount of pepper over the torn greens.
Cut uncooked bacon into small pieces.
In a 12-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Do not drain off drippings.
Stir in vinegar, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Remove skillet from heat; add torn spinach or lettuce and green onion.
Toss gently until well coated.
Turn into a serving dish.
Top with the chopped hard-cooked egg; serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Stir constantly. Mix egg yolks, cornstarch and cold milk in a small bowl.
Add to the other mixture until the sauce thickens.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cook over medium heat.
Pour into baked pastry. Top with meringue.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Peel and slice one banana per person longways.
Lay the bananas, cut side up, on a micro-proof platter.
Sprinkle brown sugar over the bananas.
Cook the bananas on High until they are hot through and the brown sugar has melted.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: bacon tomato rounds
directions: Separate each biscuit into 3 thinner layers and place on a baking stone or non-stick baking sheet. Combine rest of ingredients and place 1 tablespoon of mixture on top of each biscuit. Bake at 375 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rice with peas
directions: In a 2 1/2 or 3 1/2-quart saucepan, saute onion, bell pepper, garlic and celery until onion is just soft.
Add water and the rest of the ingredients except the parsley.
Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring occasionally, then reduce heat to low.
Stir well.
Cover and continue to simmer until rice is cooked (about 12 to 15 minutes).
Uncover.
Add chopped parsley.
Stir and fluff with a fork.

title: oreo treat
directions: Crumble cookies on bottom of an 11 x 13-inch pan (reserve 1/2 cup).
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour on top of cookies. Sprinkle with reserve.
Chill for several hours before eating.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, 5 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon; let stand until second part is ready.
Blend ingredients for 5 minutes. Grease and flour tube pan.
Alternate layers of apples and batter to make 3 layers.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs singlely, beating after each.
Sift flour before measuring.
Add other dry ingredients, then sift again.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup of hot water.
Cool.
Add strawberries and pineapple; congeal.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and put into loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: condensed milk
directions: Cooking and baking with sweetened condensed milk can be expensive, why not make your own.

title: weight watchers quiche
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze all water out. Saute onion in oil. Add spinach. Cook until all moisture is out. Beat eggs real good. Add cheese to spinach mixture.
Pour into lightly sprayed 10-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut pancakes
directions: Have on hand extra banana slices and chopped nuts for toppings.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all together, except chocolate bits.
Bake on a jelly roll pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover with chocolate bits and spread immediately.
Sprinkle with ground peanuts if desired.
Cut when cold with pizza cutter.

title: creamy lime potato salad
directions: Place potatoes and 1 teaspoon salt in water to cover in large saucepot.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat and cook until potatoes are just tender, 15 minutes.
Drain.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and mix. Add sour cream, then dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheets; press down with bottom of decorated glass that has been dipped in sugar. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rice and bouillon in shallow casserole dish.
(Rice will float some.)
Lay washed pork chops on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: donuts
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, then shortening and beat well. Add the milk.
Stir in sifted ingredients.
Chill dough for 2 hours.

title: chili - rotel style
directions: Cook beef, onion and pepper in a large stock pot until meat is browned.
Drain excess drippings.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: In a bowl sift sugar and flour.
Mix in a saucepan oleo, oil, cocoa and Coke.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry mixture.
Then add marshmallows, eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered pecan pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; beat until smooth.
Add 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla, beating until combined.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Combine 3 eggs, corn syrup, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla; beat well and pour over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until set.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: chow chow
directions: Lose 10 pounds or more weekly and feel great.
One of the secrets of the effectiveness of this 7 day plan is that the food eaten burns more calories being digested than they contain.
You can also repeat this 7 day plan without fear of feeling ill.

If followed correctly, it will flush your system of impurities and give you a feeling of well being you never thought possible. After 7 days you will begin to feel lighter because you will be lighter by at least 10 to 15 pounds and have an abundance of energy.

title: fiesta tacos
directions: In skillet, cook beef until browned, stirring to separate and break up meat. Drain off fat. Add soup and heat; divide meat mixture among the 8 taco shells. Top with lettuce, tomato and cheese. Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces.
Brown slowly in margarine. Add onion, mushrooms and seasonings.
Simmer until tender.
When tender, add cream cheese (cut cheese into cubes to melt more quickly).
Add milk and stir until cheese is completely melted. Serve over noodles.

title: indian chicken
directions: De-skin and
wash
chicken.
Peel
potatoes and cut up. Pour enough oil to cover bottom of a large (6 quart) saucepan. Place onions
and
garlic
in
oil
and cook until soft.	Add tomatoes and
all
other
spices.
Let it cook to form a thick sauce.
Add chicken
and
potatoes after sauce has thickened. Cook on
medium heat.
Add	1 cup of water.
Cook 55 minutes. Stir frequently. Serve with white rice and pita bread.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic salt.
Mix ground beef, Pizza Quick, tomato sauce, tomato paste and catsup.
Cook macaroni about 7 minutes.
Place half of mixture of ground beef in dish and then put macaroni, layer Mozzarella cheese and then remainder of ground beef.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar well. Add egg yolks 1 at a time (beat well after each addition). Sift soda and flour together. Add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk. Beat in coconut, nuts and vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff and then fold into cake mixture. This will make 3 layers. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. This will depend on your oven. Cool.

title: beef stew with beer
directions: Roll beef cubes in flour.
Saute in oil until brown.
Place in casserole dish.
Fry onions; add to casserole.
Add parsley, basil, oregano, beer, salt and pepper.
Spread both sides of bread (leftover homemade or bakery bread is best) with mustard.
Place on top of ingredients.
Cover and bake at 275° for about 3 hours.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Pour hot drippings in loaf pan.
Sift flour and salt together. Gradually stir in combined milk and eggs and beat until smooth. Pour in loaf pan.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: "road kill"
directions: Get pork roast sliced longways.
Layer roast, sausage (cut up small), onion soup and dressing.
Layer again, beginning with roast, etc.
Wrap in foil and cook on grill or place in broiler and cook slowly in oven.
Delicious.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti in half.
Cook, drain and soak in cold water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain spaghetti.
Add cubed tomatoes and cucumbers and cut-up green onions.
Mix Salad Supreme and Italian dressing together.
Mix all together well.
Keeps well for several days.
Better second day.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Place apples in cake pan (sprayed with Pam).
Mix rest of ingredients together until crumbly, then sprinkle over apples. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is crisp.
Serve warm with cream or a scoop of vanilla ice cream.
Yummy!

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat, add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolk.
Pour back into pan and cook until it boils.
Remove from burner, add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with beaten egg whites and brown.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rub a 1 1/2-quart baking dish with butter.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine; blend in flour and milk gradually.
Simmer, stirring, over low heat for 3 minutes.

Add salt and grated cheese and continue to heat until cheese is melted. Arrange potatoes in baking dish; pour cheese sauce over them and top with crumbs, which are mixed with remaining 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until crumbs brown.

title: texas trash
directions: Combine and blend butter, Worcestershire sauce, salt and garlic powder in electric skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until evenly coated.
Cover and bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 9 cups.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make sure you drain the pineapple well.
Roll in crushed walnuts and refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix the butter and graham crackers for crust; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes; cool completely.
Blend together cream cheese and sugar; spread over crust.
Add pineapple,, then the sliced bananas on top of pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and lightly top with chocolate syrup.
Decorate with cherries if you desire.
Refrigerate.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Boil together sugar, syrup, butter and water until brittle stage (300°).
Add vinegar and stir hard.
Pour into a buttered pan and mark in squares with a knife when slightly cool and not hard.

title: p-nut crunch cookies
directions: Cream the first four ingredients together.
Add and mix together with the remaining ingredients.
Cool in refrigerator 1/2 hour.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in microwave-safe container 20 seconds at a time until well mixed. Pour mixture over Chex, mixing until all cereal is well coated. Pour 1/2 of powdered sugar in large freezer bag with half of the cereal mixture. Shake until well-coated. Repeat with other half sugar and cereal mixture. Place in colander to remove excess sugar. Enjoy!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in a large pan.
Bring to boil.
Turn to medium heat and stir constantly.
Boil for 10 to 15 minutes to a soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla; stir.
Turn out into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan, greased.
Cool, then slice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt butter and mix in graham cracker crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Let cool. Cream the cream cheese and add sugar.
Spread on graham cracker layer.
Slice bananas thinly over cream cheese.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Spread large container Cool Whip over this.
Sprinkle pecan chips over and garnish with cherries.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and soda; set aside.
In saucepan, place water, margarine, oil and cocoa; bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well and set aside.
Mix together buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Add to chocolate batter.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Start icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: simple dinner rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop in greased muffin tins and cook 12 minutes at 450°.

title: cream cheese peach pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk or electric mixer on high speed until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping. Drain peaches and add to mixture with spoon. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together sugar and Crisco; add peanut butter, eggs and other ingredients.
Roll into balls and pat down with a floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add to cucumber mixture.
Let come to a boil.
As soon as mixture comes to a boil, remove from heat.
Seal in jars.

title: beef and black-eyed peas
directions: Brown beef with garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute meat, onion, celery and bell pepper in oleo until meat is browned.
Add celery and mushrooms.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Cover with frozen Tater Tots and bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: german oven pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place margarine in glass 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 5 minutes or until margarine melts and bubbles.
Put milk, flour, sugar, eggs and salt into a blender or food processor; mix until smooth.
Remove pie plate from oven. Immediately pour in mixture all at once.
Return to oven.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Lower heat to 350°.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes more (until edges are puffed and browned).
A well will form in the middle.

title: hash
directions: Boil chicken.
While chicken is boiling, cut up pork, beef, potatoes and onions.
Remove chicken from broth and add pork, beef, potatoes and onions.
Remove chicken from bones and return to broth.
When meat, potatoes and onions are cooked to hash, add other ingredients to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: beach dip
directions: Mix lemon juice with softened cream cheese and spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Spread cocktail sauce over cream cheese.
Drain shrimp; rinse well and pat dry.
Sprinkle shrimp over sauce.
Garnish with tomato and green onions.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes thoroughly and slice thin.
Layer potatoes along bottom of greased baking dish.
Layer thin slices of butter and mushrooms (cheese, if desired) with sprinkles of flour, salt and pepper, about 3/4 up the pan.
Top layer should be potatoes.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Cheddar, if desired.
Bake for about 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: nachos
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery in a skillet.
Add salt, soup and kidney beans to meat mixture and cook for 8 minutes at medium heat.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with nacho chips.
Pour meat mixture on top.
Cover mixture with remaining chips; sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Serve with taco sauce and optional toppings of sour cream, olives and guacamole.

title: pickles
directions: Pour 2 cups vinegar from jar of pickles into saucepan. Add the pickling spices and bring to a boil.
Let cool. Pour back into jar and let set for 4 days, shaking jar several times each day. Drain pickles on the fifth day well. Wipe pickles dry. Slice.
Layer pickles and sugar in a pan.
Let stand until sugar starts to melt. Stir gently until sugar is dissolved. Put pickles back into jar. (Mustard seed may be added.)

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Combine onions, bell pepper and garlic. Add shortening. Cook until golden brown. Add shrimp, salt, pepper and parsley. Cook about 20 minutes over medium heat until golden brown. Serve over rice.

title: peach buffet salad
directions: Reserve 1 cup peach juice.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water. Add peach juice.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Beat cream cheese and whipping cream slowly.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Add jello mixture slowly.
Then add peaches and pecans and mold.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add all dry ingredients together.
Add egg to mix to crumble, one at a time.
Sprinkle on apples.
Melt 3/4 stick oleo and pour over top.
Bake for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: mama's best shortcake
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a cake pan.
Save some of the sugar and melted butter to put on top.
You can add extra sugar to the top if you like.
That's rather nice.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain grease.
Put all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Stir and add water as needed to get consistency you like.

title: banana muffins(fat-free)
directions: Spray 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups with cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.

title: fiesta snack mix
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, combine corn chips and nuts.
In a small bowl, combine butter, cheese and taco seasoning mix.
Pour over corn chips mixture.
Stir until well coated. Spread mixture evenly on a baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes.
Cool completely.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
About 6 cups snack mix.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In mixer bowl, cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, mixing regularly.
Add extracts and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or two bread loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done with toothpick.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix ingredients and set aside until juices come out.
Put into pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate one hour before serving.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook about 30 minutes.
Seal in small jars.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, pumpkin, oil and water together, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.
When cool, frost.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine, sugars, egg and orange extract until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and chips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes. Let stand for 2 minutes.

title: emerald punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a punch bowl.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add a few drops of green food coloring.
Add ice and 7-Up. Garnish with lemon slices and cherries.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Place in baking dish (raw).
Add soup mix and wine.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: salmon fritters and asparagus sauce
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl. Add milk and egg; beat until smooth. Remove skin and bones from salmon and flake with fork. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Fold into batter. Fry tablespoons of mixture, a few at a time, in deep fat heated to 375° until golden brown, about 3 or 4 minutes. Drain on paper towels. Serve hot with Asparagus sauce.

title: peachy keen salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until thickened.
Blend in yogurt and whipped topping.
Stir in peaches and pecans.
Pour into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and chill until firm.

title: white cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 350 degree oven until done.

title: holiday almond loaf
directions: Soak 1/4 cup beans overnight; drain.
Whiz in blender the next day 1/2 cup beans and 1/2 cup water until thick and creamy. Combine in mixing bowl with remaining ingredients.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Press into prepared Pyrex loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: basic roll dough refrigerator rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour with dry yeast, salt and sugar.
Heat milk (or water) and margarine in saucepan until very warm (don't boil).
Add to flour mixture, along with egg.
With mixer, beat 2 minutes.
By hand, stir in remaining 2 to 2 1/4 cups flour to form stiff dough.
Cover and refrigerate up to 5 days. When ready to bake, remove from refrigerator.
Form into rolls. Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. May be used right away.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy.
Chill and serve with sliced apples, strawberries, pears or any other fruit you would like.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and cube peaches.
Slice strawberries and bananas.
Mix fruit together.
Sprinkle pudding and Tang over fruit and stir well.
Put in refrigerator at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Make gravy (according to package directions).
Add sage.
Mix chicken and peas into mixture.
Add sour cream.
Serve over rice.

title: baked salmon
directions: Rinse steaks thoroughly in cold water; pat dry with paper towels.
Place steaks in a shallow baking pan coated with vegetable cooking spray (Pam).
Brush with lemon juice.
Sprinkle evenly with dill weed, parsley and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Serving amount is 1 steak at 92 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
2 lean meat.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 2-quart pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: my sister's swiss steak
directions: Flour meat; brown in a skillet with Crisco.
In a saucepan, take 3 tablespoons of pan drippings and 3 tablespoons of flour and stir together.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Place meat in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish; pour mixture over meat.
Cover and cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add oil, eggs, and water. Beat well. Fold in the strawberries. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured bundt pan. Serve plain or with strawberry butter icing.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix peanut butter and margarine until blended.
Gradually add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chocolate bits, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in greased and floured 9-inch pan.

title: shrimp puffs
directions: Combine shrimp, celery, mayonnaise, minced onion and garlic salt and set aside.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Roll each rectangle to form a 5 x 8-inch rectangle.
Cut into 8 smaller rectangles.
Place about 1/2 teaspoon of filling on each rectangle.
Fold dough over and press to seal.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Yield: 32 appetizers.

title: venison steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces. Roll in flour; set aside. Put remaining flour, gravy mix, soup mix and beer in crock-pot. Stir together, then add steak. Cook 10 to 12 hours on low.

title: deviled chicken thighs
directions: Spread mustard on thighs, both sides, and coat with crumbs. Heat oil in Dutch oven, or deep skillet, add chicken and cook 5 minutes on each side until crisp and browned.
Add 1/2 cup reserved peach syrup to chicken.

Bring to boil, reduce heat cover, and simmer gently for 30 minutes until thighs are tender. Remove chicken, whisk in remaining peach syrup into pan drippings, stir in peaches and lemon juice. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve on rice.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Slice angel food cake into 3 layers; drain pineapple well. Reserve juice.
In a small saucepan, blend together pineapple juice, sugar, cornstarch, egg yolks and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Cool thoroughly.
Cream together butter and confectioners sugar.
Blend in cooked mixture, a tablespoon at a time.
Add well drained pineapple. Fold in 1 cup whipped cream.
Fill and top cake with mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, frost sides with remaining cream.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and spread 1/3 of mixture in bottom of a 7 x 11-inch microwave baking dish.
Layer 2 corn tortillas on top.
Combine next 4 ingredients with 1/2 of mixture over tortillas.
Repeat layers, ending with salsa mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes, rotating dish during cooking.
Remove wrap; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Let stand until cheese melts; cut into squares.
Serves 6.

title: broiled venison chops
directions: Place marinated venison loin chops on cold broiler grid. Combine melted butter or margarine and lemon juice for each chop. Brush chops with lemon butter.
Broil 3 inches from full gas flame 10 minutes.
Turn; pour over remaining lemon butter and continue broiling 5 to 8 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Stir until dissolved and mix into chopped cabbage.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on the box (making two layers).
After baking and cooling the layers, split them to make a total of four layers.

title: oriental pork
directions: Trim excess fat from pork. Combine egg, 1/4 cup chicken broth and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Beat smooth.
Pour salad oil into electric skillet to depth of 1-inch.
Heat to 375°.
Dip pork in batter. Fry in hot oil for 5 to 6 minutes or until golden. Drain and keep warm.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Serves 12.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pick over popcorn.
Boil molasses, sugar, water, vinegar and salt without stirring to 250° or until it becomes brittle when tried in cold water.
Remove from fire and add butter and vanilla. Have corn in a large pan.
Pour the syrup over it gradually, using a spoon to mix well.
Form into balls.
Four recipes use 1 pound corn.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and Karo syrup.
Add peanut butter. Stir to melt peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: pork chops with rice-a-roni
directions: Fry pork chops, then add boiling water.
Add box of Rice-A-Roni and package of sauce, mushrooms and tomato sauce. Stir up as good as you can.
Let simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: delicious potatoes
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, butter, cheese and scallions until smooth (over low heat in a medium saucepan).
Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass pan with Pam or line with butter.
Add potatoes and sauce. Top with bread crumbs; drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy casserole
directions: Cook rice and sauce according to package directions.
Stir in soup and vegetable.
Add 1/4 can of milk; top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugars, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg together as for pie crust.
Set aside 1 cup for topping.
Add baking powder, salt and soda to mixture and mix well.
Add 2 eggs and buttermilk. Beat.
Stir in chopped apples.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix chopped nuts in with reserved topping and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
(If using two 9-inch round cake pans, bake at 350° for 25 minutes.)

title: custard manju
directions: Sift
flour
and
salt together.
Add oil and mix well, adding the
cold	water.	Form
the
dough into little balls, about the size of a walnut.
Flatten it out and wrap a ball of "An", completely	covering
An.
Place them on a cookie sheet and brush the tops with evaporated milk, using a pastry brush. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: cream puff ring
directions: Bring water and margarine to boil.
Add flour and salt.
Stir vigorously over low heat until forms balls.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Drop 10 (1/2 cups) of dough on greased cookie sheet to form ring.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet to rack.
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Reserve 1/2 cup cheese mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and bananas; chill.
Cut top of ring.
Fill with whipped cream mixture.
Replace top.
Add remaining sugar, chocolate and milk to reserved cream cheese mixture.
Mix well. Spread over ring.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Roll each slice thin with rolling pin.
Spread cream cheese on bread slices.
Place one asparagus spear in each slice of bread.
Roll bread around asparagus.
Place bread rolls in baking dish.
Spread melted butter on top.
Bake in 350° oven.
Turn several times to brown all sides.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and beat well.
Cook at 450° until brown about 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream in a bag
directions: In a small baggie, combine milk, half and half, sugar, vanilla and chocolate syrup.

title: sharon's famous lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put wafers in plastic bag and beat with a meat cleaver until fine (save several whole wafers that can be placed around the outer rim of the pan).
Put wafer crumbs in pan and add stick of melted butter.
Combine butter and crumbs; press into bottom of the pan.
Stand whole wafers around the sides of the pan.
Mix the milk, juice and eggs in a bowl.
Bake the crust for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Place filling in pan.
Simple, but delicious. You can top it with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: pecan chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and eggs in bowl.
Add margarine, vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 pie shells. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
These pies may be made ahead and frozen.

title: roast beef n' swiss tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread each tortilla with Caesar's dressing.
Cover entire surface.
Top each tortilla with lettuce leaf, roast beef, Swiss cheese and red onion.
Roll up each tortilla tightly.

title: pistachio nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer except pudding. Fold pudding in with spoon. Set aside. Prepare Sugar Mixture.

title: grandmother's sugar cookies
directions: Roll out, cut with a glass.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) on a greased baking sheet until golden. Store in airtight container.

title: chewy choc-oat chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine and
sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour and baking soda; mix.
Stir in oats, morsels
and	nuts.
Drop
tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool on rack.

title: peanut blossoms cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix until dough forms in large.
Shape into balls, using a rounded top for each.
Roll balls in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie instantly with a Hershey candy Kiss.
Press down firmly so cookie edges crack.

title: pizza crust
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water; stir until dissolved.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar and salt.
Add egg and 1 tablespoon oil; stir until smooth and glossy.
Stir in 2 cups flour.
Knead dough 10 minutes.
Put in a greased bowl.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down and divide in half.
Makes 2 pizza crusts.
Brush lightly with oil.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix in 3-quart pan.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Place 5 quarts of popped corn in a greased roaster pan and pour sauce over. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Mix every 15 minutes.
Spread on 2 or 3 cookie sheets to cool.
Break up a bit.
Store in airtight container.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Meanwhile, fry bacon to a crisp.
Break into small pieces.
Arrange sliced baked potatoes into a boat style. Take inside out, saving shell.
Mix potato whites with bacon, applesauce, sour cream, butter and chives.
Stuff potatoes and wrap in foil.
Rebake at 250° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4. Use any leftover stuffing for a dip.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat 1/2 cake mix with butter, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining mix, nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoons about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until edges are set (centers soft).
Cool 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack to cool. Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Saute meat, onion and bell pepper.
Add all other ingredients and simmer approximately 1 hour, until cabbage is tender.
Season to taste.

title: tutti-frutti punch
directions: Combine all ingredients together, adding ice cream last.

title: dundee tea bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until light.
Beat in vanilla and eggs. Add sifted dry ingredients and fruit; mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan lined with waxed paper on bottom.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn out on rack and peel off paper; turn right side up and brush with glaze.

title: strawberries and almond cream
directions: Carefully wash berries; drain on paper towels.
Cut a deep "X" from pointed end of each berry to 1/4-inch from stem end.
Gently spread apart to make petals.
Set aside on a serving plate. Prepare pudding according to package directions except use only 3/4 cup milk.
Gently fold whipped cream and extract into pudding. Pipe pudding mix into strawberries from a decorating bag with a large tip.
Serve immediately.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together except cheese.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to pkg. directions. Divide the batter into three 8 or 9 inch pans that have been sprayed with Pam. Bake according to directions. Remove from oven and allow to cool.

title: mexican corn for diabetics
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomato, in large nonstick skillet.
Cover; cook over medium heat 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 minutes or until tomato is heated thoroughly.
One-third cup = 1 bread.

title: easy sunday chicken
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle rice on bottom.
Mix soups and milk.
Pour over rice.
Lay raw chicken pieces on top and sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° about 2 hours or until rice is tender and chicken is done.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Rinse beans.
In a medium saucepan, combine beans and 3 cups water.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain beans.

title: aebleskivers
directions: Beat egg yolks; add water.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
With cast iron aebleskiver pan you can make this tantalizing pastry in 5 to 10 minutes right on top of your stove.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients and cook in unbaked pie crust in moderate oven (350°).

title: raspberry custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1 tablespoon preserves, then 6 berries, in each of six 3/4-cup custard cups.
Whisk sugar, eggs, yolks, vanilla and salt to blend in medium bowl.
Heat half and half over medium heat until tiny bubbles form around edge of pan. Gradually whisk half and half into egg mixture.
Evenly divide custard mixture in cups.
Set cups into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour enough hot water to reach halfway up the sides of cups. Bake for 35 minutes.
Remove from water.
Cool 10 minutes. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: icebox cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on cake mix.
Bake in long pan, 13 x 9-inches.
When done take out, cut cake down middle, then cut one-half in strips.

title: coconut mounds
directions: Melt butter in saucepan until golden brown. Gradually stir in sugar, coconut and milk. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and put in refrigerator. Melt chocolate and paraffin wax. Shape mounds and then use tongs and dip into chocolate.

title: nutty apple cobbler
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Combine apples with topping and flour.
Spoon into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Separate each biscuit into 2 thin biscuits and place on top of apples.
Mix sugar, nuts and butter and drizzle over biscuits. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased iron skillet. Bake at 350° until done.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 350° oven in pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: polish chruseiki
directions: Beat eggs until thick; add sugar, salt and rum or vodka. Combine flour and baking powder and place on a flat surface.
Make a well in the center.
Add butter.
Blend together, using tips of fingers.
Build up mixture and pour eggs-sugar liquid into the center.
Using a fork, start stirring the liquid, adding the flour mixture into it, a little at a time.
Knead dough until smooth. (Dough tends to be sticky, but do not add additional flour, unless necessary.)
Turn dough over at first with a pastry scraper.
Cut dough into 4 parts and roll out paper thin on a lightly floured board.

title: thai ribbons
directions: Soak 30 six-inch long bamboo skewers in water. Combine teriyaki sauce, ginger root, oil, garlic and red pepper.
Cut steak across grain into 1/4 inch thick slices.
Place beef in plastic bag; cover with marinade.
Turn over several times for 15 minutes.
Remove beef from bag and thread each slice onto skewer. Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 2 minutes on each side. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Makes 15 appetizer servings.

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, at medium speed, beat together, until smooth, the cream cheese, 1 egg, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over the bottom of the pastry shell.
Sprinkle with the pecans.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth in electric blender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with tostada chips.

title: blueberry-rhubarb breakfast sauce
directions: In saucepan, ring rhubarb and sugar to a boil; boil gently ten minutes.
Remove from heat; add pie filling and mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Store the sauce in jars or freezer until ready for use.
Serve with pancakes, waffles, toast or English muffins.
Yields 7 cups.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven. (I used Equal, 3 egg whites, 3 whole eggs.
May substitute half the shortening with applesauce.)

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion and pepper and brown slightly.
Place meat, onions, peppers, garlic and seasonings in large Dutch oven.
Mix together thoroughly.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce and cook for 30 minutes.

title: pasta with seafood sauce
directions: Saute onion, garlic and parsley in a little oil.
Add the tomato sauce, the chopped peeled tomatoes and wine.
Also add the salt, oregano and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp, clams and squid.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Turn off heat and cover.
Let sit for several minutes to blend flavors.
Cook pasta according to package directions and serve the sauce on top of the cooked pasta.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Save some coconut for top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let stand 5 minutes.
Mix white and brown sugar and eggs.
Add to oatmeal mixture.
Combine flour, soda and salt; then add to mixture.
Add 1/2 bag chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 bag chocolate chips and nuts over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(Don't bother trying to test for doneness because chocolate chips will be melted and confuse the test.)
Cool before cutting.

title: tiger butter
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with wax paper.
Melt white chocolate and crunchy peanut butter together in a double boiler or microwave.
Pour in pan and spread to cover the whole pan.
Next, melt the dark chocolate and pour on top of white chocolate and peanut butter mixture.
Take a spoon and swirl together.
Put pan in the refrigerator for about 5 to 8 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: chicken pot pie(for one large kettle)
directions: Add enough ice water to make easy rolled out dough, approximately 1 cup.
Cut into squares.
Drop into boiling broth. Season to taste, add deboned chicken after pot pie squares are cooked.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together in a saucepan.
Boil until thick as ketchup.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Scatter croutons over bottom of a 9-inch glass pie plate. Overlap alternate slices of tomatoes
and Mozzarella cheese on top in a circular pattern to cover.
Sprinkle with basil, chives and pepper.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Remove from oven; spoon dressing on top.
Let stand 5 minutes for flavors to develop.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, vanilla, sugar and eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients, alternating with milk, vinegar and bananas.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Spray loaf pan with Pam. Bake for 60 minutes or until top starts to crack down the middle. Can also make muffins; bake for 26 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in oleo.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper.
Heat through, but do not brown.
Mix in rice; spread 1/2 of the cabbage in a 2-quart casserole (lightly greased).
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with tomato soup over top.
Dot with butter.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: herb bread
directions: Combine all ingredients above.
Add enough milk to get the consistence that you want, mix well.
Pour into a large skillet or muffin pans.
Bake in 400 degree oven until golden brown.

title: stuffed crab(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Rinse and thoroughly drain crabmeat to remove excess salt. Melt 5 tablespoons of butter in a heavy skillet over low heat. Add bell pepper, onion, celery and garlic. Saute, stirring frequently, until tender.
Stir in crabmeat, cayenne and pepper.
Stir in 2/3 cup of the bread crumbs.
Blend well and correct seasonings.
Grease scallop shaped baking shells or an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex baking dish with ample butter.
Add crab mixture.
Mix remaining 1/3 cup bread crumbs with the parsley. Sprinkle crumb mixture over the crab. Sprinkle with paprika and dot with 5 teaspoons of butter.
Cut into small pieces.
Bake 20 minutes and serve hot.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Add garlic; add rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil, then turn down to simmer.
Cover and continue to simmer until cabbage is done.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Fry onion and celery in oil.
Rinse rice and boil 1 minute. Combine chuck and pork.
Add egg and celery mixture.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic.
Place meat mixture in cooled cabbage leaf and roll.
Cover with tomato juice and sauerkraut.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours in large roasting pan.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except clams; then add clams.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: taffy squares
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Stir in flour.
Spread evenly on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pizza crackers
directions: Place crackers on cookie sheet.
Spread 1 teaspoon ketchup on each cracker and add pepperoni and any other desired toppings. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Easy for kids and a good healthy snack.

title: easy lime pie
directions: Combine limeade and condensed milk.
Add sour cream, stir until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip; add food coloring.
Spoon into pie crusts.
Chill about 3 hours until set.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Let stand.
Beat eggs slightly. Beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in alternately with apples and sugar mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into a greased and floured pan (13 x 9-inches).
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix and beat together the eggs.
Add Wesson canola oil, sugar, buttermilk and soda mixture, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, vanilla, flour, prunes and English walnuts.
Pour into a well greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 48 minutes. Let set in pan for 10 minutes and then turn out.

title: ranch crispy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine dressing mix and bread crumbs in plastic bag. Add chicken and shake. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes (until juices run clear).

title: almost candy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl cut margarine into cake mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over bottom of cookie sheet.
Press lightly.
Sprinkle with chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour condensed milk over all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: mexican dip
directions: Chop onions and tomato.
Grate cheese.
Layer as listed and eat with Doritos.

title: pineapple lemon-lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in
boiling
water.
Add cold water and can of pineapple.
Add
remaining
ingredients and chill until firm. Serves 16 to 20.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: In the top of double boiler over hot, not boiling water, melt the chocolate with half of the peanut butter.
Stir until smooth. For extra creaminess, add the 4 tablespoons butter or margarine. Put remaining peanut butter in the top of another double boiler over simmering water.
Melt the peanut butter until it has a pouring consistency.
Place 24 miniature muffin paper liners inside cupcake or muffin tins.
Pour 1/2 of the chocolate mixture equally over the peanut butter.
You now have a bottom layer of chocolate, then peanut butter and finally top layer of chocolate. Let stand at room temperature about 2 hours to set.
Store them refrigerated in a covered container up to a week or frozen for months.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten egg yolks.
Sift together 3 cups of flour and baking powder and add to mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff and add.
Mix fruit and pecans with 1 cup of flour.
Mix this into the batter with a fork; pour into a tube pan and let stand in oven covered with foil.
Place pan of water on shelf under cake.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours, then 1 hour more at 300°.
Let stand 20 minutes before turning out on plate.

title: macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, matzo meal and salt in mixing bowl. Stir in egg whites and extract; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets immediately.

title: english toffee
directions: Mix sugar, water and butter in saucepan on medium-high until boils (stir occasionally).
Reduce heat to medium and stir moderately until mixture reaches caramel color.
Pour into greased shallow pan and immediately sprinkle chopped chocolate and then nuts over hot mixture.
Let cool and break into bite size pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: deviled crab pate(makes 1 cup)
directions: Let butter stand at room temperature, until it is soft enough to spread easily.
Check crab meat to make sure all shells are removed.
Put all ingredients into blender; blend at high speed until a smooth mixture is reached.
Form into a ball.
Chill in the refrigerator.
Makes 1 cup.

title: curried chicken dish
directions: Dry chicken breasts.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add 2 cloves garlic.
Saute garlic until brown.
Throw garlic pieces out and saute chicken breasts at 300° until done.
Debone and remove skin. Cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Cook 1 cup converted rice in 1 can chicken broth.
Cook until rice absorbs broth.

title: snappy santa fe meat loaf
directions: Saute onions, peppers, celery and garlic in skillet until soft.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Shape mixture into a loaf and place in loaf pan.
Bake at 375°
for 45 minutes until brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and sift all dry ingredients.
Add chopped onion.
Combine the beaten egg with the milk; add to dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep, hot grease where fish are cooking.
When done, they will float.
Drain well.

title: cheese log
directions: Cream; shape into log.
Sprinkle with paprika (chill).
Serve with party rye bread or crackers.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in sheet pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain. Mix all other ingredients together, reserving some of the onion rings for top. Add vegetables.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fried turkey
directions: Dry and season turkey (inside and out).
Heat oil until temperature reaches 375°.
Place turkey in oil.
Cook 3 1/2 minutes per pound.
Place on a platter.
Cook 1/2 hour before carving. You must use a thermometer to check temperature of oil. Oil must be kept at 325° while cooking.

title: guacamole-est dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Chill until ready to serve.
Place an avocado pit in the dip to prevent dip from discoloring; remove before serving.
Makes 3 cups.

title: easy rolls
directions: Put Crisco, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add boiling water. Let cool to lukewarm.
Mix yeast with 1/2 cup warm water.
Add eggs, then flour.
If mixing with mixer, stir in last 2 cups of flour by hand.
The more you beat, the better they are.
Pour a little oil over dough.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Knead down.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise and bake at 400°.

title: custard pie
directions: Scald milk.
Mix together the eggs, sugar, vanilla, spices and salt.
Pour scalded milk into mixture and blend well.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 375° for 20 minutes.
Pie is baked well when knife inserted in pie comes out clean.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Prepare round cans by cutting wax paper to fit in the bottom. Four 1 pound coffee cans work well.
Sift flour, salt and cinnamon.
Cover raisins with water and bring to a boil.
Skim out of water and put in large bowl.
Add butter and soda.
Cover with boiling water.
Cool.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Flour nuts and add.
Bake in cans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine stuffing mix, butter and water.
Mix lightly.
Put 1/2 of the mixture in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Combine turkey, onion, chives, celery, mayonnaise and salt.
Put on top of first mixture.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour over all. Sprinkle with other half of stuffing mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Spread top with mushroom soup.
Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Return to oven and bake another 10 minutes.
Use a 12 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Serves 8.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets; cut into thin strips.
Reserve juice.
Add water to measure 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Pour into saucepan and bring to a boil; add all but beets.
Stir.
Chill until partially congealed. Stir in beets.
Pour into wet 1-gallon mold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Combine in saucepan the sugar, margarine and milk. Cook slowly for 5 to 8 minutes, stirring. Add vanilla.
Pour over plain cake or gingerbread.

title: no cook divinity
directions: Combine dry frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in a small mixing bowl.
Beat on highest speed until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to a larger bowl; gradually blend in confectioners sugar on lowest speed.
Stir in nuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto wax paper.
When outside of candy feels firm, turn over and allow to dry at least 12 hours.
Store candy in an airtight container.
This is very good.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix well.
Put in a graham cracker crust.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: sweet onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Thinly slice onions. Saute onions in butter until soft and transparent. Remove from heat. In separate bowl, combine eggs, sour cream, salt, and peppers until smooth. Pour onions into pie shell. Pour egg mixture over onions. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then lower oven temperature to 350° until top is lightly brown, about 30 minutes.

title: matthew celeberto's bread pudding
directions: Pour scalded milk over bread and let stand.
In a separate bowl, mix together all other ingredients.
Then combine with bread and milk.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Stand casserole in a plate of water.
Bake at 375° for an hour or more.

title: great cranberry salad!
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Mix all other ingredients and serve.

title: easy skillet taco pie
directions: Brown beef in large skillet and drain. Stir in taco seasoning and water. Layer refried beans on half-broken taco shells, 1 cup cheese, salsa and corn on top of beef. Top with remaining taco shells and cheese. Cover and cook slowly for 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: simple caramel pecan pie
directions: Toast pecans and coconut in oven until light brown.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together and pour into crust.
Pour pecans and coconut over pie and top off with as much caramel as you like.

title: dewberry cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a casserole in which you plan to bake.
Wash and drain berries and add 3/4 cup sugar.
Coat well by stirring and let stand.
Sift flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and stir well.

title: pull buns
directions: Add sugar, oleo and salt to scalded milk. When lukewarm, add the dissolved yeast, eggs and just enough flour to make a stiff batter. Cover and let rise until double in bulk. Work down. Let rise again. Pull off ball size of walnut; dip in melted oleo. Roll each ball in mixture of the last 3 ingredients. Place these balls in ungreased angel food cake pan. Let raise for 30 minutes. Bake for 11 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes. Turn pan upside down immediately.

title: italian filled cookies
directions: Start with 4 1/2
cups	flour.	Make a well and add all other ingredients into
the
center.
Mix well, blending flour from the sides
of
the
well,
adding
more
flour if needed. Dough should be	easy
to
handle, not sticky.
Cut dough into five sections. Roll
each	section
to
inch	thickness. Spread with grape jam (or any other) and sprinkle with raisins and nuts.
Roll the dough
or 4 times) and place the seam side down on a
greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put layer of asparagus, then soup, then cheese; repeat.
On top put sliced eggs and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Cream butter or oleo, add sugar.
Beat well.
Sift together baking powder, baking soda and flour.
Add eggs to beaten butter and sugar.
Mix well. Add vanilla and sour cream.
Then add dry ingredients.
Butter 10-inch tube pan.
Put in half of the batter, sprinkle with half of nut mixture.
Put in remaining batter.
Sprinkle with rest of nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Partially drain all fruit.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stir in pudding mix (dry).
Keep overnight in refrigerator.
Stir once before serving.

title: bean soup
directions: Cut up the bacon and brown to a crisp. Add the water to the vegetable soup mix. Add the pork and beans. Cook 1/2 hour.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add soda to boiling water and set aside.
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Alternately add buttermilk and flour.
Fold in boiling water and soda mixture.
Add bran flakes and all-bran.
Spoon in muffin tin and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Mix will last 6 weeks in the refrigerator.)

title: chicken reuben
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and garlic powder (if desired).
Place chicken in casserole dish and pour in sauerkraut.
Place cheese on top of chicken, then pour dressing on top.
Cover with foil and bake about 45 minutes, depending on thickness of chicken.
You can add potatoes to casserole for a 1 dish meal.
It may look terrible, but it tastes great!

title: summertime fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Great for dipping strawberries, bananas, apples, pineapple, peaches, etc.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil first 7 ingredients in large soup pot for 30 minutes. Beat milk and flour until smooth; slowly stir into vegetable pot and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
Add Cheddar cheese, mustard and pepper.

title: country beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Drain all beans.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Mix all ingredients and put in crock-pot.
Simmer 8 to 10 hours uncovered.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add kidney beans and salsa. Continue cooking, uncovered, over medium heat for 20 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.
Place 1/2 cup tortilla chips on one side of salad bowl and 1 cup of lettuce on other side.
Top with 1/2 cup meat mixture.
Sprinkle salad with tomatoes, olives and shredded cheese.
Top each with 1 tablespoon of guacamole.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Place on paper towel and press until slightly moist.
Combine spinach, mayonnaise, sour cream and vegetable soup mix, then add water chestnuts; mix well.
Cover and chill mixture several hours.
Serve with assorted raw vegetables.
It's also good served as a salad dressing.

title: orange cheese salad
directions: Bring pineapple, sugar and water to a boil.
Dissolve gelatin in hot mixture.
Cool in refrigerator until it is the consistency of egg whites.
Add cheese and nuts.
Fold in dessert topping. Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: cabbage delight
directions: Boil cabbage.
Add bouillon cubes, corned beef and apples. Mix well.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt fat.
Brown garlic and onion slightly, using high heat. Add meat and brown, then add pepper, celery, tomatoes and seasoning.
Cover and cook on high until steaming.
Stir mixture. Sprinkle rice on top.
Do not stir after adding rice.
Cover and turn switch to low and cook without removing cover for 30 minutes. Cook off 15 minutes.
May substitute 1/2 package of spaghetti for rice.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add mushrooms, gravy mix and water; stir well.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add sour cream. Simmer for 5 minutes on low heat.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add egg and flavorings; mix thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375° (quick moderate).
Divide dough in half and roll out on lightly floured pastry cloth to 3/16-inch thick. (Roll very thin for crisp cookies.)
Cut as many cookies from each rolling as possible.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until delicately golden.
Makes 5 dozen 2 to 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and salad oil; add eggs.
Stir well.
Combine next 5 ingredients; stir into oil mixture until smooth.
Add carrots and pecans.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake for 45 minutes at 400°.
Makes 1 skillet.

title: quick hamburger stew
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Drain. Add soup and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until heated.
Great with cornbread. Quick and easy.

title: robby's sugar coated pecans
directions: Beat egg white until foamy. Add pecans and toss well. Combine sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over pecans. Spread on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 300 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: glazed spice bars
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Dough will be stiff.
Pack into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken for fifty
directions: Mix flour and seasonings.
Roll chicken in flour.
Brown chicken in hot shortening.
Place in large pans.
Bake, skin side up at 325°, until tender.
Check to see if juices run clear, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add syrup and salt; beat well. Beat in eggs, one at a time, and add pecans.
Pour into a 9-inch pastry lined pie pan. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: mrs. heacock's sugar cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and add flour.
Roll into ball shapes and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Don't crowd on pan as they spread as they bake.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Strange ingredients; but a very tasty cookie.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Fry the onion or garlic slightly in the oil; add other ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Liquid should be reduced about 1/2 and sauce should be well blended.
Dip all meat except fowl in sauce before roasting or broiling or baste with sauce during roasting either in oven or on outdoor grill.

title: green slime popcorn
directions: Measure popped corn into large bowl, set aside.
Combine sugars, corn syrup, water, vinegar and food coloring in 2-quart or larger saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, to 260° on candy thermometer or hard ball stage (a few drops of syrup dropped into very cold water can be formed with your fingers into a hard ball).
Reduce heat to low, stir in margarine until melted and mixed in.
Pour syrup over popcorn; stir until well coated. Spread out on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break apart if necessary.
Store in airtight container.

title: b. j.'s coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Pour cream of coconut over warm cake.
Cool.

title: peach jello ice cream pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in whipped topping.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Chill or freeze until firm.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar replacement and salt in top of double boiler.
Beat until frothy.
Beat in milk and add vanilla bean.
Cook and stir over simmering water until mixture is thick and vanilla bean is dissolved.
Cool completely.
With electric beater, beat well and then fold in topping.
Pour into freezer trays; cover with waxed paper and freeze for 1 hour.
Scrape into large bowl and beat until smooth and fluffy.
Return to freezer trays.
Cover.
Freeze firm.
Yield: 1 1/2-quart (1 1/2 L).

title: christmas tags
directions: Cut out picture from Christmas card, then with pinking shears, cut construction paper about 1/4 inch larger than the picture. Hold 2 pieces together and punch a hole in the top with hole punch.
Take approximately 4 inches of ribbon, double it over, put the looped end through punched hole and pull the two cut ends through the loop and tighten.
Tie tag to package.
These can be made from any size Christmas card.
Write to and from on the construction paper.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, margarine and sugar. Add eggs. Beat well.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Line 24 muffin tins.
Divide batter into tins.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
After cool, fill with fruit filling.

title: mexican beef and rice
directions: Cook beef, onion and chili powder in skillet over medium heat until onions are soft.
Stir in rice and tomatoes.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese.
Serve with cornbread or corn chips.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: our version henry bain sauce
directions: Mix all together, chop up large pieces of fruit in the chutney and again taste until you get it right.

title: walnut bread
directions: In mixing bowl sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening.
Stir
in 1 1/4 cups of the walnuts. Add milk, eggs
and
vanilla.
Mix
just
until blended.
Turn into
greased and
floured
x
5-inch
loaf
pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup walnuts on over top.
Bake at 350° for 60 or 70 minutes or until it tests done.

title: ham delights
directions: Split Pepperidge Farm party rolls horizontally.
Spread top and bottom with a mixture of all the ingredients.
Place shredded ham and Swiss cheese squares on each roll.
Wrap in foil and heat 10 minutes at 400° or until cheese begins to melt.

title: john's hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add egg and enough sweet milk to hold
shape.
Drop
by teaspoon into hot fat and cook until golden brown.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Mix margarine, curry powder, honey and prepared mustard.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Cover and bake 45 minutes in 325° oven. Turn chicken breasts over and bake 45 minutes more, uncovering last 10 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine all the ingredients into a crock-pot and cook for 4 hours on high or 5 1/2 hours on medium heat.
On stove top, bring to a boil and simmer for 1 1/2 hours on medium heat.

title: oriental steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except steak; add steak.
Marinate steak in sauce for 2 hours.
Broil 3 inches from heat to desired doneness.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: oven baked stew
directions: In small bowl, combine soup and milk; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine chicken, salsa, chilies, chili powder and 2 tablespoons of soup mixture.
To make enchiladas, along one side of each tortilla, spread about 1/3 cup of chicken mixture.
Roll up each tortilla, jelly-roll fashion; place seam side down in greased 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Spread remaining soup mixture over enchiladas.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; add salt and pepper and stir.
Add milk and Cheez Whiz.
Stir until Cheez Whiz melts into potatoes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni by package directions.
Brown onions and ground beef.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes, oregano and garlic; simmer for a few minutes.
In layers, start with sauce in baking dish.
Add 1/2 macaroni; top with more sauce and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Add the rest of the macaroni.
Pour rest of sauce over casserole; top with remaining cheese.
