Garnish with 3 or 4 slices of green pepper.
Bake at 300° to 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
In large bowl, mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add drained beans, green pepper and onion.
Marinate for 24 hours before serving.
Stir occasionally while marinating.

title: shrimp rice
directions: Brown bacon crisp; dice onion, green pepper and celery and saute in bacon grease.
Cook rice.
After rice is done, add sauteed ingredients and grease with shrimp and crumbled up bacon. Sprinkle small amount soy sauce.
Cook on low until shrimp is done.

title: crispix mix
directions: Combine Crispix, nuts and pretzels in large microwave bowl. Combine garlic salt, onion salt, lemon juice and butter.
Mix with Crispix mixture.
Microwave for 4 minutes.
Stir after 2 minutes. Spread on paper towel to cool.

title: baked potatoes on the half shell
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.
Cut into halves lengthwise and remove the insides of potato.
Mash insides well; season with salt, pepper and butter.
Add enough milk to moisten.
Beat until fluffy and creamy.
Refill the shell. Sprinkle grated cheese on the top and a little paprika.
Brown in oven.
Serve hot.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain and return to skillet.
Add tomato soup and enchilada sauce.
Heat.
Stir well.
Add meat sauce mix to each tortilla.
Sprinkle on some cheese; roll each enchilada up. Place seam-side down in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour remaining meat mixture over tortillas.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: bible pudding
directions: Combine B, C, D and F.
Stir in vigorously A and pour into well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle E on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until well done.

title: orange marmalade
directions: Slice oranges and lemon very thin and remove only the seeds. To each pound of sliced fruit add 3 pints of cold water.
Let stand in a cool place for 24 hours, then boil until skins are tender. Set aside for 24 hours.
Weigh.
To each pound of mixture, add 1 1/2 pounds granulated sugar and boil until it jells.
Skins are transparent.

title: cream cheese crescents
directions: With electric mixer, mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Set aside.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cottage cheese and cream cheese together.
Spread evenly in serving dish and sprinkle taco seasoning over entire area. Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top and serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in bag.
Break biscuits in quarter pieces; put in bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Shake and coat well. Grease and flour tube pan.
Place biscuits in pan in layers. Between each layer, sprinkle nuts.
(Any sugar and cinnamon left in bag may be poured in pan.)

title: margaret's recipe for uncle ray's favorite bread
directions: Combine cut up dates with the hot water with soda mixed in and let stand.
Mix together the sugar, egg, flour, baking powder, salt, nuts and vanilla.
Add the date mixture.
Makes a large loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
In saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook briefly, then gradually add cream, stirring constantly, until sauce has thickened.
Add corn and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Build in layers in order.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix and butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange apple slices over base.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Spread evenly over apples. Sprinkle reserved topping over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until topping is golden brown and bubbly.
Makes 12 to 15 squares.
Serve warm.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Place broccoli in large bowl; drizzle dressing over broccoli and toss gently.
Add remaining ingredients and toss gently. Cover and chill 8 hours; toss.
Can serve on lettuce leaves.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together first five ingredients. This syrup is cold, do not heat.
Use sterilized jars (any style because they don't have to seal).
Put cucumbers and some onions in jars.
Since syrup is cold it has a tendency to settle, so stir as you pour.
Just refrigerate and pickles will last a long time when kept cold. These are easy and real good.

title: italian asparagus
directions: Cook and cover asparagus in a small amount of boiling water for about 4 minutes.
Drain and arrange in a serving platter.
Combine tomato and next 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Spoon mixture over asparagus.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings. Each serving contains 31 calories and 0.5 fat.

title: helen's mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Bone and cut up into bite size pieces.
Mix chicken, onion, cheese, garlic salt, chili powder, and Rotel (mashed).
Soften tortillas in boiling chicken broth.
Line tortillas in baking dish.
Add mixture.
Pour soup over this mixture.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside. Measure bran flakes and milk into mixing bowl; stir to combine. Let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until most of moisture is absorbed. Add egg and shortening; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients to bran flakes mixture, stirring only until combined.
Fill greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups 3/4 full.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 400° about 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: southwestern layered dip
directions: On a flat round serving tray, layer each of the following in order: Cream cheese, refried beans, guacamole, sour cream and salsa.
Top with shredded cheese, jalapeno, black olives, green onion and tomatoes.
Serve cold.
Add chips to the sides for garnish.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Use correct proportions (do not skimp).

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and 1 stick oleo; blend with an electric mixer on medium speed until mixture resembles corn meal. Press crust mixture firmly and evenly into prepared baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes or until lightly golden brown. Combine rest of ingredients in mixing bowl in order listed, blending well after each addition. Pour filling over baked crust; return to oven. Bake for 25 to 28 minutes or until filling is set. Cool completely on wire rack before cutting into 2-inch squares. Makes 24 squares. Tastes like individual pecan pies.

title: pepperoni cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into ball. Refrigerate.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine corn starch sugar, salt and cherry juice in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils. Add margarine, cherries and lemon juice.
Pour into a lined 9 inch pie pan.
Cover with top crust, make several slits and seal and flute edge.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg-sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix and spread in greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: pumpkin bread(do in order of recipe.)
directions: Combine and mix first 5 ingredients.
Add and mix remaining ingredients.
Grease (no flour) 3 coffee cans.
Pour 1/2 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream
sugars, butter and peanut butter.
Beat in eggs, milk and
vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir into
egg mixture.
Shape
into
balls.
Roll
in
additional granulated sugar.
Place
on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven
for 10 to 12 minutes.
When removed from the oven, immediately press a chocolate candy into each.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients (sugar, flour, cocoa and salt), then add milk slowly.
Beat well until smooth.
Cook over hot water until thick.
Add egg yolks and cook 5 minutes over hot water, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool, then pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue; bake at 325° for 20 minutes until slightly browned.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Dip tortillas in butter and line bottom of casserole.
Mix chicken and green chilies.
Layer 1/2 of chicken, green onions and cheese.
Repeat, ending with tortillas.
Mix one can cream of chicken soup and 1 soup can of milk.
Pour on top of casserole. Wrap with foil.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars and peanut butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to peanut butter mixture.
Chill dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Flatten with a floured fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 6 dozen.

title: coconut angel delight
directions: Slice cake 1/2-inch thick.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and flour. Add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat until coats spoon.
Dissolve gelatin in warm water.
Pour gelatin in custard. Cool in refrigerator about 1 hour.
Beat egg whites; fold into cooled custard.

title: king's arms tavern cream of peanut soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until soft, but not brown. Stir in flour until well blended.
Add chicken stock, stirring constantly, and bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat and puree in a food processor or blender.
Add peanut butter and cream, stirring to blend thoroughly.
Return to low heat and heat until just hot, but do not boil.
Serve, garnished with peanuts.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and rinse in cold water.
In large bowl, toss macaroni, olive oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked corn
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Pour milk over cracker crumbs.
When moist, add eggs.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour into a buttered dish; bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Stir the sugar and flour, chocolate and salt together in a skillet and make a small well; add egg and slowly mix into powder mixture.
Turn burner on low heat.
While cooking and stirring, slowly add milk and water.
Cook until thick and bubbly, stirring almost constantly.
Add vanilla and a small amount of butter.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove seeds and membranes; rinse.
Cook peppers in enough boiling water to cover for 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: low-fat gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix (unprepared), 1/2 cup Promise and 1/4 cup Egg Beaters in bowl by hand.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend well and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Brown onion in hot fat; add meat and brown until crumbly.
Add seasonings, soup and water.
Bring just to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Pour corn bread batter over meat in skillet.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bean casserole
directions: Add all together and bake or put in crock-pot for 4 hours or more on low.

title: chicken francesa
directions: Soak chicken in milk 10 minutes.
Mix breadcrumbs, cheese and parsley.
Dredge each piece of chicken in the breadcrumb mixture. Pour oil into skillet and braise chicken quickly on each side until lightly browned.
Do not overcook.
Put chicken in a lightly buttered baking dish.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Place 1 slice of lemon on top of each chicken piece.
Remove all but 1 tablespoon of oil from skillet, leaving residue from chicken.
Add wine and boil until liquid is reduced by 1/2.
Add lemon juice and chicken broth.
Boil until liquid is reduced by 1/2 and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until liquid bubbles, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add garlic and rosemary.
Remove meat and simmer onions until soft.
Sprinkle in brown sugar and stir.
Return meat.
Add wine.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add water and bouillon.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Spoon into pie crust. Chill overnight or place in freezer for about 15 minutes to chill, if serving immediately.

title: basic pie shell
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the flour and salt, then cut in the shortening with a pastry cutter or 2 knives until the mixture resembles coarse meal. Stirring with a spoon, gradually add the water until a ball of dough is formed. Wrap the dough in a plastic wrap and chill until ready to use.

title: screwball cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and form into a hole.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and spread with icing.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and cinnamon together and press into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Arrange bread slices tightly on top of the mixture layer.
Mix eggs, milk and salt well and pour over the bread layer.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: In a large bowl with mixer at low speed beat first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently or beat vigorously 300 strokes by hand.
Batter will be very thick.
With a spoon stir in the apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and frost with whipped cream.

title: sausage rissoto stuffing
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage; drain, crumble and set aside.
In a large saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Add onions until tender.
Add rice and stir constantly, coating until rice is opaque, but brown.

title: fu's pepper steak
directions: Cut beef in serving pieces or narrow strips.
Brown slowly in hot beef fat about 15 minutes.
Add onion and garlic.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir and cook about 2 minutes longer.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water.
Add to meat.
Cover skillet and let simmer until meat is almost done, 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Remove garlic slice.
Uncover skillet; add combined cornstarch, water and soy sauce stirred together and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, 5 minutes longer.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: 3 minute microwave fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and vanilla.
Cut butter up.
Cook on High in microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir vigorously. Add nuts and vanilla and pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Refrigerate 1 hour or freeze 20 minutes.
Cut into small squares to serve.

title: swedish pecan balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape dough into balls the
size
of a walnut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at	275°
for
to
minutes.
Roll cookies in powdered confectioners
sugar while still hot.
Place on rack to
cool. After cookies have cooled, roll them in confectioners sugar again.

title: winter succotash
directions: Drain vegetables; add remaining ingredients and heat in double boiler. Serves 6.

title: impossible coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend sugar and flour.
Add to eggs along with milk, vanilla and coconut.
Turn into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans. This mixture forms its own crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Add butter or oleo, 3/4 cup sugar, salt, raisins, 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and milk to noodles.
Mix Ricotta cheese, 1 egg, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon together.
Mix together with the noodle mixture.
Bake in buttered 14 x 9-inch Pyrex dish at 350° for 1 hour.
While hot, loosen edges and cut but let cool 10 minutes before removing.
May need to cover with aluminum foil to keep from browning too fast!

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix together all of above; batter will be stiff.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Press dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until golden brown (about 25 minutes).
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Cook spinach according to package directions and drain well.
Mix sausage, spinach and other ingredients in large bowl.
Stir until evenly mixed.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crisp on top.

title: sausage squares
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet, stirring until sausage is crumbly, drain will.
Add cheeses, parsley, 1 egg and tabasco sauce.
Mix well.

title: cinnamon crisp cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Mix in egg and molasses. Stir in flour with soda and cinnamon; blend well.
Drop by teaspoons or roll in round balls onto greased cookie sheet. Press them down just a little.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Dough keeps well in refrigerator for a while.

title: mrs. roosevelt's lobster soup
directions: Add 2/3 can of full-cream milk for each can of soup.
Brown lobster meat in butter, add to soup mixture and warm slowly.
Add sherry to taste just before taking off stove.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Mix ketchup and sugar.
Pour over chicken in crock-pot.
Slice onion and place on top.
Cook on high one hour and low for 7 hours.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on a plate.
Add 2 cans small shrimp (drained) and 1/2 bottle chili sauce.
Mix shrimp and sauce; spread over mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Chop pecans to almost a sand consistency.
Add carrots and onions from the can of jalapenos.
Blend in approximately 1/4 cup of the juice.
Fill up each of the jalapeno halves.
Makes about 40 or so.

title: granny's fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste. Dip in beaten egg and roll in self-rising flour.
Let sit 30 minutes. Fry in hot oil until well done.

title: easy chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and arrange in baking dish.
Place sliced chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cook on low and heat until bubbly, stirring until thickened.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Cool and then chill.
Fold in whipped cream, orange liquor and beaten egg whites.

title: mock almond roca
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Butter bottom.
Put down a layer of saltine crackers.
Bring brown sugar and butter to boil and cook for 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes, then spread smooth.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all liquids.
Mix all ingredients together and chill well (best result if chilled overnight).
May be served on lettuce or as a vegetable main dish.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Combine the brown sugar and soy sauce. Pour over the chicken wings and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Place in crock pot when serving.

title: hot pickled wieners
directions: Wash and dry wieners; punch holes in them with fork.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Cover with sauce mixture:
remaining ingredients (except vinegar).
Put in airtight jar or bowl and cover with white vinegar.
This sauce keeps 2 or 3 weeks and you can keep adding wieners.
Marinate at least 24 hours before using.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat milk until almost to a boil.
Add crackers, 4 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper.
Bring to a scalding point (do not boil). Add oysters and cook until edges curl (just a few minutes). Ladle soup into bowls.
Swirl 1 teaspoon of butter into each bowl. Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook the broccoli and onion in the chicken broth and milk for about 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until broccoli is tender.

title: dutch rhubarb pie
directions: Place cut rhubarb in shell.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over rhubarb.
Sprinkle with melted butter or margarine. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes; then reduce heat to 375° and bake for 30 minutes.
Cover crust with foil if it becomes too brown during final 10 to 15 minutes.

title: boeuf en daube
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, remove and crumble into small pieces. Dredge meat in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown meat on all sides with garlic in bacon fat.
Add bouillon, wine and a dash of salt; bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Transfer into casserole, add vegetables, herbs and bacon.
Cover and bake at 350° until fork-tender (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: low-fat french fries
directions: Cut the potatoes into strips.
Toss thoroughly in 2 large egg whites; sprinkle with spice
Put on cookie sheet pan sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Bake in oven at 400°.
Turn French fries often.
Bake for about 15 to 20 minutes, until tender and golden brown.
(Can spray with Pam a couple of times while baking.)

title: dilled shrimp spread
directions: Pour tomato juice into a 1 to 1.5-quart pan.
Sprinkle with gelatin and let stand for 5 minutes to soften.
Place pan over low heat and cook, stirring, until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat and let cool.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in pan.
Add some water to make paste.
Add remainder of water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: scallops and mushrooms in shells
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt 1/4 cup of the butter in a small skillet and add the mushrooms.
Cook, stirring often, until the mushrooms are wilted and give up their liquid.
Add the shallots and garlic and cook briefly.
Spoon the mixture into a mixing bowl.
Let cool briefly, then add 2 tablespoons of the remaining butter, scallops, bread crumbs, parsley and salt and pepper. Blend well.
Use the mixture to fill 6 seafood shells.
Arrange the filled shells on a baking dish or cookie sheet.
Melt the rest of the butter and pour it over the mixture in the shells.
Place in oven and bake 10 minutes.
Run the scallops under the broiler until nicely browned.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Mix cole slaw mix and green onion and set aside.
Break up both packages of Oriental noodles into small pieces.
Saute margarine, noodles, almonds, sesame seed and 1 package seasoning mix from noodles (save the other package for the dressing) for approximately 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: belgian panapiss(fruit cake)
directions: Combine water, sugar, raisins, cinnamon and Crisco in large bowl; set aside.
Combine eggs, vanilla, baking soda and flour. Combine both mixtures.
Add the salt and the nuts.
Bake in greased bread pans at 375° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large bowl mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in oats.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until coarse crumbs form.
Stir in walnuts.
Set aside.

title: corn dogs
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder, salt and dry mustard.
Cut in shortening, using two knives scissor fashion, until mixture becomes coarse crumbs. Mix egg and milk. Add to dry mixture, mixing well. Insert wooden skewers in one of wieners.
Heat oil to 375°. Coat wieners with batter.
If batter is too thick, add 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.
Place 2 or 3 wieners in oil for 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot with ketchup or mustard (optional).

title: baked corn with cornbread mix
directions: Mix all together.
Bake, uncovered, in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour until golden brown.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Cut off tops of peppers; remove seeds and membrane.
Precook pepper cups in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes, then drain. Sprinkle inside of cups with salt.
Brown meat and onion in fat. Add tomatoes, rice, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper. Cover and simmer until rice is almost tender, about 5 minutes. Add cheese.

title: smoked sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage if desired or mix all ingredients and put in rice cooker.
Makes 4 servings.
One serving = 3 1/2 protein, 1 bread and vegetable.

title: tomato relish
directions: Skin tomatoes.
Place in jars; seal.
Place jars in roaster pan with water around the bottom of jar.
Place in oven 35 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven off and let cool.
Pretty!

title: oven baked beans casserole
directions: Brown your hamburger meat.
Mix with all ingredients.
Bake in oven for about 30 minutes.
Cook some rice to put over it.

title: six and one minute icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in top of double boiler with bottom double boiler filled with boiling water.
Set timer for 6 1/2 minutes and beat with mixer while cooking.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until of spreading consistency.

title: benson's orange-cranberry bread
directions: Place butter in cup.
Add boiling water to butter to equal 1/4 cup.
Add fresh orange juice to make 3/4 cup.
Add egg to dry ingredients, then add liquid and mix to blend.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Mix and pour into a greased and floured bread pan. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cranberry-pecan muffins
directions: Combine the cranberries and 1/4 cup sugar; set aside.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and 1 cup of sugar into a large bowl.
Cut in the shortening with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in the pecans and lemon rind.
Beat eggs in a small bowl until light.
Add liquid all at once to flour mixture, stirring only until moist.
Fold in cranberry mixture. Spoon batter into lined muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: swedish ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill dough.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Cook above until boiling.
Remove from heat; add 2 tablespoons oleo and 1/2 cup pecans.
Pour mixture over sweet potatoes.
Can make night before.
Heat in oven at 375° for 25 minutes or until bubbling.

title: candied violets
directions: In one bowl, beat egg whites until frothy.
Put sugar in another bowl.
Pick up violet by stem; dip in egg whites and then in sugar.
Totally cover.
Put on waxed paper.
Snip off stem. With toothpick, open flower petals.
Dry in 200° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until sugar crystallizes.
Remove flowers with spatula or fork.
Store in airtight container with waxed paper between layers.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Brown sausage in frypan; drain drippings. Add biscuit mix and grated cheese to sausage. Mix well and make into 1 inch balls. Press in pan and bake at 375° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In soup pot, combine and boil the ingredients on low for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: tricky meat balls
directions: Grate onion and green pepper.
Stir into rice.
Add salt, pepper and tiny bit of garlic.
Using fork, stir lightly through ground meat.
Form into ball the size of walnut.
Add 1/2 cup water to tomato soup and heat baking pan.
Drop balls into hot soup and bake 1 hour.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Drain and pour into 3-quart casserole dish.
Add all remaining ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Top with chow mein noodles; cover and bake 1/2 hour.

title: barbecued turkey
directions: Marinate turkey 12 to 14 hours and barbecue.

title: talagrini primavera
directions: In a large pan, boil water and cook noodles.
Diagonally cut asparagus into 1 inch lengths.
In a wide frying pan over medium heat melt butter.
Add the ham, asparagus, carrot and zucchini. Cook the mixture, stirring occasionally, for 3 minutes without a lid.
After that cover the pan and cook for 1 minute longer.
Now add the green onions, peas, basil, salt, nutmeg, pepper and half and half to the mixture.
Increase the heat to high and cook until the liquid begins to boil.
Mix with noodles and top with parmesan cheese.
Makes 3 to 5 servings.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and slice eggs on top.
Mix soup and broth and pour over all.

title: pudding cones
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
After it sets, spoon into ice cream cones.
Top with Cool Whip, sprinkles, nuts and a maraschino cherry.
Serve immediately.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill for 5 hours.
Top with pie filling.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; spread on bottom of a 9-inch pie plate or similar type
dish with sides.
Top with remaining ingredients, ending with cheese on top.
Serve with taco chips.

title: orange mallow yam bake
directions: Arrange yams and orange slices in a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oriental beef and vegetables
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. Add all Ramen noodle seasoning packages and noodles, broken up into small pieces. Add water and stir. Then add stir-fry vegetables. Cook until vegetables and noodles are tender. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve in bowl the jello, very hot water, sugar and lemon juice.
Place in 9 x 12-inch dish and refrigerate until partially set.
When partially set, add pineapple juice, crushed pineapple, orange rinds, celery, nuts and cranberries.
Refrigerate.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Put ingredients into blender.
Cover.
Blend 10 seconds. Yield:
1 1/4 cups, about 10 calories per tablespoon.

title: guadalupe river dessert
directions: Pat 1 cup flour, 1 stick margarine and 1 cup chopped pecans into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: swedish cake
directions: Mix all together and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until very thick.
Add sifted dry ingredients; beat smooth.
Add dates, vanilla extract and nuts. Bake in waxed paper-lined 9 x 13-inch pan in moderate oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
While warm, cut in 1 x 4-inch bars.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 2 dozen bars.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and scrub. Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through. Put them in a baking dish. Fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with herbs. Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes. Sprinkle with cheeses and bake for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken breasts on a cutting board; cover with waxed paper.
Lightly pound to flatten the breasts.
Do not cut through meat.
Discard waxed paper.
Lightly salt and pepper each breast. (Cheese may need to be folded to fit on breast.)
Roll the breast, jelly roll style; secure with a toothpick.
Combine cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Melt margarine; dip rolled breasts in the margarine, then in the cracker crumb mixture. Place in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: healthier baked stuffed shells
directions: Mix together turkey, fentil or sage, and garlic powder.
Mix well to get the taste of Italian sausage.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a greased baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: ham-swiss cheese sandwiches
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add mustard, onion and poppy seed.
Blend.
Spread on cut sides of buns.
Place ham and cheese on each buns.
Wrap each sandwich in foil.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Good way to use leftover ham.
Can be frozen to be used later.
If frozen, bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Cook mushrooms with chicken broth 20 minutes.
Add cream, lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste, parsley and onion.
Simmer approximately 1/2 hour.

title: chinese chicken with peppers and onions
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1/2-inch squares.
Clean peppers; cut into 1-inch chunks.
Slice the onions into thin quarter pieces. Spray a wok or frying pan with Pam; heat until quite hot.
Add the ginger, cayenne and chicken to pan; stir until chicken is thoroughly cooked, about 3 minutes.
Remove to a serving dish. Spray pan with more Pam, if necessary.
Add the onions and peppers; stir-fry until onions become slightly transparent.
Return chicken to pan.
Add soy sauce; stir 1 minute.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Serve with rice.

title: date nut bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, beating until light and fluffy. Add vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients a little at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Bake in a greased, square pan at 375° for 30 minutes.
When done, cut into bars.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine potatoes, flour, sugar and egg. Blend together, using a fork.
Form mixture into balls, 1-inch in diameter.
Pour oil into a 10-inch frying pan. Heat to 375°.

title: candy bar pie*
directions: Place 1/3 cup of peanuts evenly over bottom of pie crust. Drizzle 2 tablespoons caramel syrup over peanuts.
Combine pudding mix, dry milk and water, using a wire whisk.
Pour over peanuts. Chill about 2 hours.
Spread whipped topping evenly over chilled pie.
Sprinkle remaining peanuts over topping.
Drizzle remaining 1 tablespoon caramel syrup over
top.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, wine vinegar and sugar; toss with broccoli, raisins, onion, bacon and sunflower seeds.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep well in the refrigerator.

title: green beans
directions: Put bacon in iron skillet.
Cook until just hot.
Pour two cans of green beans with liquid into the skillet.
Drain the other two cans and pour beans in skillet.
Cook until all juice cooks out.
You can add garlic salt, thin onion rings, new potatoes.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain.
Stir remaining ingredients in with warm carrots until coated.
Salt to taste.

title: orange salad
directions: Stir together orange Jell-O and Cool Whip.
Then add cottage cheese.
Drain pineapple and oranges.
Fold in pineapple and oranges.
Put into refrigerator, only take out when eating.

title: milky way cake
directions: Cream 1/2 cup margarine and sugar. Sift together flour and soda.
Break eggs in a large bowl. Beat until light.
Add creamed sugar and beat well. Add flour, soda, buttermilk and nuts.
Beat well.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine and candy.
Add to mixture. Beat well.
Pour into Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in hot water. Add sherbet. Stir well. Combine in a bowl the oranges, pineapple, cherries and pecans. Pour sherbet mixture over this. Stir and chill until congealed.

title: fruit slush salad
directions: In 3-quart nonmetallic container, combine bananas, pineapple, juice concentrates, ginger ale and cherries; mix well.
Grate peel and squeeze out juice of orange and lemon; add to pineapple mixture.
Cover; freeze 8 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve in small dessert dishes.

title: marianne's lite italian chicken
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and warm.
Brush sauce on both sides of chicken and then sprinkle with paprika.
Marinate overnight in sprayed oven dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
If desired, garnish with paprika and lemon slices.

title: henderson's dessert
directions: Place pie filling in a 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix and pecans on top of filling.
Top with melted butter.
Do not mix. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: fat potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients. Place in a large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered. Uncover and bake for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: jumbo cornburger
directions: Combine beef with next 5 ingredients and spread half of mixture in an 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch round, ovenproof dish or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients except tomato and cheese; spoon over meat.
Cover with remaining meat mixture. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Last 5 minutes, arrange tomatoes on top and sprinkle with cheese.
(I use more cheese and cut tomatoes in small pieces.)

title: old norm's meat dressing
directions: Dice the onions; cook in some oil.
The oil should have some olive oil mixed in proportions of 1/4 olive oil to 1 of cooking oil.
Cook onions, pepper and celery until there are no crunchies. Add in the spices in the onion mixture; simmer for 14 minutes. Cook the meat; pour off the liquid.
Mix the two meats and onion-spice together.
Add water and stir.
Mix, taste and brag until it is mushy.
Cook either inside the turkey, or bake in the oven until the crust is formed on top of the dressing, in bread pans.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Combine in mixing bowl and beat 4 minutes. Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in 2 loaf pans in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across the grain into thin strips 1/8-inch thick. Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Toss and set aside.
Heat oil in large frying pan or wok.
Add beef and toss over high heat until brown.
Taste meat, if not tender, cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to pan.
Stir and cook until thick.
Add tomatoes and heat throughly.

title: quick beans
directions: Dump everything into skillet and mix well.
Cook covered for 1 hour on low heat.
Remove cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and onion.
Add Sweet 'N Low and dressing; mix well.

title: mustard glaze
directions: Combine ingredients.
Brush mixture on ham (or other meat, vegetables, etc.) frequently during the last hour of baking. Makes 1 cup (enough for 10 to 15 pounds ham).
Can use glaze on roasted chicken, turkey or as a dipping sauce for shrimp or chicken nuggets.

title: raspberry filled white chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in small pan over low heat. Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup of the vanilla chips. Let stand.
Do not stir.

title: pretzel cheese cake dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Save a little for topping.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Put in refrigerator.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar, then add Dream Whip.
Put on top of pretzel crust.
Cover with 32 ounces cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle with remaining crushed pretzels.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 15 to 20 minutes in muffin pan.
Use either cupcake papers or grease pan.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Put raisins and water in 2-quart saucepan.
Cover and cook until all liquid is absorbed.
Raisins will be plump.
Add remainder of ingredients, mixing well.
Bring to a gentle boil and cook to a whipped cream consistency.
Let cool slightly and pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue, using whites from eggs in recipe.
Brown slightly and serve warm or chilled.

title: broccoli, bacon and mushroom salad
directions: Steam broccoli until tender but still crunchy; cool.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Cool on paper towels and then crumble. Combine broccoli, bacon, and mushrooms in a large bowl.
In a small bowl combine remaining ingredients to make dressing.
Pour over the broccoli mixture.
Toss to combine. Chill for at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Halve squash and cook in microwave 5 minutes.
Scrape out squash.
Saute onion, green pepper and bacon.
Drain off grease. Add tomato, zucchini and microwave 5 minutes.
Add bread crumbs, egg (beaten), salt, pepper and cheese.
Fill squash shells and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Combine soup, milk and 1/2 package of onion soup mix.
Place 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add rice on top.
Top with raw chicken.
Top with other half of milk mixture.
Sprinkle remaining onion mix on top.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion; mix with remaining ingredients. Cook on grill.
Makes about 12 (6-inch) pancakes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Beat sugars, shortening, egg and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes before removing from sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: veggie pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and chill. Add other ingredients to taste; mix well. Keep refrigerated until ready to use.
Must do ahead.

title: microwave red snapper
directions: Over low heat, in saucepan, add lemon juice, water and butter. Simmer until butter is melted.
Season fish with all other seasonings.
Place the bay leaves in bottom of medium microwave dish.
Add fish and pour lemon butter sauce over fish.
Cover.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes, then place in microwave for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Stir in soup, cheese and broccoli.
Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and brown.

title: barbecued ribs - western
directions: Combine all ingredients, bring to boil and cook, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes.
Dips ribs into sauce and grill or roast 40 to 45 minutes, or until tender, basting often and turning to brown evenly.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Beat together. Add 1 cup hot tap water and 2 tablespoons poppy seed; beat. Pour into well greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust by pressing graham cracker crumb-margarine mixture into long casserole dish.
Layer as follows: pudding, bananas, pineapple, Cool Whip and pecans.
Decorate with cherries.

title: krispie marshmallow squares
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in double boiler. Add vanilla. Beat thoroughly to blend. Put Rice Krispies in bowl and pour on marshmallow mixture, stirring briskly. Press into shallow buttered pan. Cut into squares when cool. Nuts and coconut may be added.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt butter.
Add softened cream cheese and blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill completely. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool.
Cut chicken meat into small pieces.
Grate the cheese.
Mix the broth and chicken soup.
Saute the chopped chilies in butter along with some chopped onions

title: jello shots
directions: Boil hot water per Jell-O directions.
Add Jell-O powder; mix well.
Mix 1/2 cold water with 1/2 booze.
Mix well.
Let set in fridge until firm. Put on cookie sheet.
Cut into squares.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: rice krispie cheese wafers
directions: Let cheese and oleo reach room temperature.
Cut in flour and cayenne.
Add Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press into flat wafers with tines of a fork.
Cook approximately 12 minutes at 350°.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix Wink to pineapple juice.
Add crushed ice.

title: vegetable medley salad
directions: In a large straight sided salad dish, layer half of each bread crumbs, green peppers, cabbage, cucumbers, tomatoes, celery and Onion Dressing.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine all the ingredients together and pour into a HOT, greased 9-inch square pan or iron skillet. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cut butter into flour, sugar and salt.
Add egg yolk and coconut and mix.
Spread in a 9 x 13 pan.
Spread jam over top evenly.
Beat egg white with the 2 tablespoons sugar.
Layer egg white mixture over jam.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: In mixing bowl combine stuffing, sour cream and spinach.
Form into long patties and roll 1 slice of ham around each patty.
Place into oiled or Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make 4 cups basic white sauce:

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with dressing mix.
Put half of mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over dressing and arrange chicken on top.
Put a fourth of the dressing mix on top of the chicken and spread cream of chicken soup over dressing.
Put remainder of dressing mix over the top of soup.
Pour chicken broth over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with chopped cabbage.

title: veal stew with cauliflower
directions: Dredge meat in flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet; add meat and brown it.
Pour off pan drippings.
Add onions, celery, water and thyme.
Bring to a boil; simmer for about 1 hour.
Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Add to stew; fold in gently.
Simmer 15 minutes longer until cauliflower is tender.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk over very low heat, stirring, so it will not lump.
Cook to a very thick paste.
Let it thicken, but not scorch.
Let cool.
(After it gets cold, it gets sort of like cold Cream of Wheat, but don't scream and say "What have I done?" That's a normal reaction the first time you make it.)

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine baking powder and flour; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes and invert to cool completely.
Frost.

title: mohines chicken curry(chicken curry bombay)
directions: Fry finely chopped onion in butter until brown.
Add all spices to yogurt and tomato sauce; mix well.
Pour spice mixture over chicken pieces.
Cover and bake in oven temperature of 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until well done.
A little water may have to be added to chicken while baking.
Serve over rice.

title: autumn pumpkin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare one crust pie shell.
Mix all the ingredients with a wire whisk until smooth.
Put mixture into pie shell and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: chantilly potatoes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes.
Whip the whipping cream until stiff.
Season it with salt, white pepper and cayenne.
Combine it with grated cheese.
Spread mashed potatoes in casserole dish. Cover with the whipped cream mixture.
Bake at 375° until the cheese is melted and the potatoes are lightly brown.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix and form into small balls about the size of a walnut; saute over medium heat until done; drain.
Place meatballs in a chafing dish or crock-pot.
Pour a sauce made from 12 ounces of chili sauce and 10 ounces of grape jelly over the meatballs and heat thoroughly.
Simmer in crock-pot.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: In small bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press mixture into bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan.

title: aunt debbie's cracker barrel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, baking powder and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Fold crackers and pecans into egg whites.
Bake in greased pie plate for 30 minutes at 350°.
Chill. Garnish with Cool Whip and pecans.

title: no crust peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour well.
Add milk and butter; mix well.
Add peaches and vanilla.
Pour into deep baking dish and cook until golden brown at 350°.

title: overnite casserole
directions: Mix in the evening.
Refrigerate and bake following day at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great for working moms!

title: baked artichoke spread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place all ingredients in the food processor and puree until smooth.
Pour into shallow baking dish and bake 30 to 45 minutes or until light brown on top.
Serve with tortilla chips, French bread or crackers.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Cream after each one.
Add flour and cream, flour and cream; mix well.
Let flour be last ingredient you add.
(Also, let butter, eggs and whipping cream stand at room temperature before beginning to make cake.)

title: santa's whiskers
directions: In bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cherries and nuts.
Form into 2 rolls 2-inches in diameter and 8-inches long.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap and chill overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Rolls can be kept in refrigerator for 2 weeks or frozen even longer.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Blend sugar and margarine.
Heat till boiling.
Add milk and boil four minutes.
Cool.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla. Beat until smooth.

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, then crumbs. Reserve 1/3 c. of crumb mixture for garnish.
Pat remaining crumbs firmly on bottom of 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 300 degrees for 12 minutes.
Cool.
In a large bowl, mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Stir in pie filling and fruit cocktail; pour over crust.
Top with whipped topping and crumbs.
Freeze 4 hours. Remove from freeze 20 minutes before cutting.

title: dream delight
directions: Step l:
Combine nuts, flour, sugar and oleo.
Mix well. Spread evenly in bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix together. Put in 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and seasoning; drain off grease.
Add beans and mix well.
Butter casserole dish and cover bottom with sauce.
Line dish with tortillas; add meat mixture.
Top with tortillas and rest of sauce.
Add cheese on top and water around edges.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese melts.

title: brownies
directions: Heat chocolate and margarine in microwave until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is melted, also.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and stir by hand.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef & ham loaf
directions: Mix well and bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: poor man roast
directions: Line electric skillet with bacon.
Place hamburger patties on bacon.
Add potatoes, onions and carrots.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in dish.
Put chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle on onion soup.
Mix mushroom soup, milk and water together; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover last 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chocolate chips and almond bark except 2 squares on High 2 minutes; stir.
Continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth.
Stir every 20 seconds.
Add marshmallows, cereal and nuts.
Pour onto a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle coconut over pizza.
Microwave remaining almond bark and oil in a 1-cup measure for 1 minute.
Stir. Continue microwaving 30 seconds to 1 minute or until smooth, stirring every 15 seconds.
Drizzle over pizza.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into wedges.
Store at room temperature.

title: crab mousse
directions: Heat and stir mushroom soup and cream cheese.
Add gelatin and cold water.
Beat well with mixer; add mayonnaise and beat on 1st speed.
Add celery, green onion and crab.
Mix lightly.
Add a couple drops of Tabasco.
Oil mold and let stand 6 hours or more. Serve on crackers as a spread or with raw vegetables as a dip.

title: soft shell tacos
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine hamburger, Ro-Tel and chili in large pan and simmer.
Melt Velveeta and whipping cream in microwave. Mix all together and pour over chips.
Top with onion, lettuce, tomato and olives.

title: ole time tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs; slowly
add	sugar
and oil.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix slowly.
Add flavor and mix well.
Add flour to
handling,
pinch	off
and
pat flat onto sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in preheated 450° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery together.
Do not dilute canned soups. Mix all the ingredients together in one casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika, if you want.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook and chop chicken breasts.
Marinate in light French dressing overnight.
Next day, mix the chicken, the celery, Miracle Whip, almonds, sliced water chestnuts and green onion. Put in a baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cover with the Cheez Whiz. Cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350° or until hot.
Add 1 cup French fried onion rings on top the last 5 minutes.

title: curried pork with apples
directions: In a wok, melt 3 tablespoons butter or margarine to 350°.
Add pork; cook and stir 6 minutes.
Remove from wok and reserve. Reduce heat to 300° and melt 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Add the onion; cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add the apple; cook and stir 2 minutes.

title: not yo' mama's banana pudding
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2 baking dish with a layer of cookies, on top of the layer of cookies, slice the bananas and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl mix the pudding mix and the 2 cups of milk and set aside.
In another bowl mix the sweetened condensed milk and cream cheese until smooth, stir in the cool whip topping.
Add the cream cheese mixture to the bowl with the pudding and fold in until all the pudding is mixed in.
Pour mixture over the bananas and cookies, lay the rest of the cookies on top and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cranberry-grape salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water until skins pop.
Add sugar.
Then add lemon Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple with juice.
Add grapes.
Put in ring mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain and keep liquid.
Melt butter over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until blended and smooth.
Add onion until cooked, but not brown.
Add liquid slowly.
Stir to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Add seasonings, cheese and milk.
Stir until melted.
Combine with spinach in casserole dish.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly in bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Set aside.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; put in deep casserole dish. Combine the next 4 ingredients; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Dot with the margarine on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes. Uncover; bake for 10 minutes.

title: creme de menthe squares
directions: Bottom Layer:
In saucepan, combine 1/2 cup of the butter and the cocoa; heat and stir until well blended.
Remove from heat. Add 1/2 cup of the powdered sugar, the egg and vanilla.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Press into bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: mama's sweet potato souffle
directions: Heat sweet potatoes to a boil and drain. If you use plain yams, boil 25 to 30 minutes and drain.
Add sugar, butter and orange juice. Beat well. Add enough milk (1/4 cup or more) to make creamy.
Put in baking dish. Top with marshmallows.
Brown at 350°.
Check often; sometimes it browns fast.

title: tired wife cake
directions: Prepare a sheet cake pan by either spraying with Baker's Joy or greasing and flouring pan.
Layer apple pie filling, crushed pineapple (with juice) and dry cake mixture.
Pour melted butter over top and sprinkle coconut and nuts on top of layers.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 35 to 45 minutes).

title: barbecue brisket
directions: The night before cooking, trim excess fat off both sides of brisket.
Sprinkle both sides with the three seasonings; place in large baking pan and pour Liquid Smoke over top.
Cover with plastic wrap and foil; refrigerate overnight.
Six hours before serving, remove plastic wrap and re-cover with foil.
Place in preheated oven at 300° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.
Remove from oven and pour off marinade.
Slice with electric knife across the grain. Place back in pan.
Pour your favorite barbecue sauce over meat. Re-cover with foil; place back in the oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until sauce is warm.

title: sugar-free raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins until soft; have at least 1 cup liquid; let butter melt in raisin and liquid.
Mix together next 6 ingredients and add to raisin mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: army style baked beans
directions: Mix together hamburger, pepper and onions in mixing bowl. Place mixture into skillet.
Cook on medium setting until done. Drain, so that mixture can be placed in large mixing bowl.
Add enough brown sugar until sweetened.
Add Tabasco sauce to desired taste.
Too much may make it unable to eat.
Place in baking dish in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Be sure it doesn't dry out too much while baking.
Take out of oven.
Ready to eat in 5 minutes.

title: vallie rogers' sugar pudding
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add oil, then flour, milk and vanilla. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350°.

title: john's deli roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 550°.
Put meat in oven for 5 minutes per pound in shallow baking pan.
Turn oven off. Leave roast in oven for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with apples, pears, bananas.

title: garden veggies
directions: Slice squash thin; cut pepper in strips.
Slice onion thin. Melt oleo; saute first 4 ingredients until tender.
While these are cooking, cut up tomato.
When squash is done, put in tomato and let heat from veggies warm them.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Serve immediately.

title: pecan millionaires
directions: Melt caramels and milk in microwave on Medium heat.
Add pecan halves.
Drop by tablespoons onto buttered cookie sheet. Refrigerate until set.
Dip in melted chocolate chips and paraffin. Put on waxed paper until cool.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as package directs; drain.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk. Bring to boiling point, stirring, then reduce heat and simmer mixture 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese and the macaroni.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake 15 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.
I use extra cheese.

title: mike's surprise
directions: Crumble Gorgonzola cheese onto the Boboli; sprinkle chopped walnuts over cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly and starts to turn brown.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms and dry onions in butter in a saucepan. Add salt,
pepper
and
flour.
Cook
1 minute.
Add milk and cream gradually,
stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened. Add sherry
just
before
serving.
Makes 6 (1 cup servings). Each serving is 385 calories, 6.2 protein and 31.0 grams fat.

title: dilled nibbles
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet over low heat; stir in Rice Chex and toast until lightly browned.
Turn often.
Mix salt, dill weed and cheese together.
Sprinkle over Rice Chex and stir well. Store in tightly covered container.

title: party ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, combine soup and milk, stirring until smooth.
Add onion, mustard and sour cream, stirring to combine well.
In prepared casserole, layer half of noodles, ham and sauce.
Repeat.
Toss bread crumbs with butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.
(You can also put potato chips on top, instead of bread crumbs.)

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture.
Can be refrigerated for days.

title: lane cake
directions: Cake:
Mix sugar and margarine; add flour, milk, beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Pour batter into greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(May use white or yellow cake mix instead.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: In your large Tupperware mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and flavoring and mix.
Add oil and dry ingredients.
Chill overnight or all day.
Form into small balls. Flatten with fork or glass dipped in sugar. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit topping
directions: Beat egg; add pineapple juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil and cook for about 5 minutes.
Refrigerate until cold. Serve over any combination of fruit.
I like the pineapple chunks that the juice was drained from, bananas, white grapes, peaches, etc.
Fruit can be fresh or canned.

title: homemade bisquick mix
directions: Stir baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and sugar into flour.
Sift together 3 times into large bowl.
Cut in the shortening until mixture resembles consistency of corn meal. Store in covered containers at room temperature.
To measure the Master Mix, pile into measuring cup lightly and level off.
Makes 13 cups.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In saucepan, stir together 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Add egg yolks and milk; stir with wire whisk until well blended.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Continue cooking and stirring 2 minutes, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Blend together the oleo, brown sugar, white sugar, pudding, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour and soda; add to the creamed mixture.
Add the chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned on top.
Cut into bars.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses; beat well. Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with the coffee to dry ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Use 1 tablespoon sugar per 3/4 cup berries.
Slice the other fruit.
Combine with berries.
Mix cream cheese, whipping cream and juice in blender.
Pour over fruit mixture.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking sheet that has been greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Loosen edges immediately and turn upside down on a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar. Carefully remove paper while cake is still hot; roll cake and towel lengthwise.
Cool on wire rack.
Unroll cake; remove towel and spread with cream cheese icing and roll again.
Slice and refrigerate.

title: lemon cake-pie
directions: Beat eggs for 1/2 minute, add flour and milk gradually until well blended.
Add salt and sugar, mix thoroughly, until mixture has a smooth running texture.
(If too thick, add milk, if too thin, add small portion of flour.)

title: slushy punch
directions: In a 2-gallon plastic bucket dissolve 3 small package of lemon flavored gelatin in 9 cups of boiling water.
Blend sugar in water and bring to a boil. Add sugar to jello mixture and cool.
Mix bottle of lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Cover with foil and freeze.
Remove from freezer at least 3 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale and mix.
Serves 50.

title: popovers
directions: Mix together and put into greased muffin tins, 1/2 or less full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Fill with whipped cream or pudding.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix well the melted shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add to other ingredients.
Add chips and nutmeats.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Mix baking soda into flour and add alternately to sugar mixture with 1/2 cup of the lemonade.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°. Brush hot cookies with remaining lemonade concentrate.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until done.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Bake in large baking dish on 350° for 45 minutes, covered with foil, then 15 minutes uncovered.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese (11 ounce) until light and fluffy.
Blend in 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add in the egg whites.
Spoon it into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until the filling is settled.
Drain cherries (reserve 1/2 cup of the juice). Combine the juice and food coloring, 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until its thick (let it cool). Arrange cherries over cheese filling.
Spoon over the cherries. Chill until its time to serve.

title: doggy stew
directions: Cook hot dogs, potatoes, onion and parsley together.

title: pat's wieners
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours.
If you use long hot dogs, cut into small pieces.

title: ms. foster's minestrone
directions: Bring 1 quart water to boiling in 3-quart saucepan.
Add the white beans (marrow, Great Northern, white kidney or navy).
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let beans soak for 1 hour. Then return to low heat and simmer beans, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Drain and set aside.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cook at least one day ahead. Better if refrigerated 2 or 3 days before serving.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Combine butter and onion.
Cook over medium-high for 3 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup water and remaining ingredients, except wieners.
Cook on high for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add wieners and cook on high for 3 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except shrimp and rice.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for about 30 minutes.
Stir in shrimp; heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: apple snow
directions: Pare and core apples.
Cook 6 apples in 1/4 cup water until soft.
Rub through sieve; add 1/3 cup sugar.
Fold in egg whites, lemon and cream.
Simmer apple slices in 2 cups water and 2 cups sugar until transparent, but not soft.
Crumble sponge cake; place in 8 serving dishes.
Heap with apple slices; top with Snow mixture.
Chill and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple lime salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in hot water.
Add jello and dissolve thoroughly.
Chill until thick.
Whip milk into mixture.
Add nuts and chill until firm.

title: no bake banana split cake
directions: Drain pineapple; set aside.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Put all ingredients in top of double cooking pot over cold water.
Turn on stove to medium-high heat.
Beat continuously with electric mixer until frosting stands in peaks, approximately 7 minutes.
Spread on cake.

title: honey almond carrots
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine carrots and water.
Cover; cook over medium heat until carrots are tender (8 to 10 minutes). Drain; add remaining ingredients.
Heat through (1 to 2 minutes).

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Cook
sweet
potatoes
until soft, then mash very fine. Season mashed
sweet
potatoes
with
salt,
sugar and melted butter. Shape
potato mixture around a marshmallow.
Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Dip balls in slightly beaten egg whites and roll in	corn
flakes.
Place
in a greased baking dish and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and roll out on waxed paper.
Spread on peanut butter.
Roll up and cut thin. Refrigerate.
Enjoy!!

title: phyllo chicken
directions: In a shallow dish, combine mayonnaise, scallions, parsley, half of garlic, lemon juice, salt and pepper. In a small saucepan over medium heat, melt butter with remaining garlic. Brush one pastry sheet with melted garlic butter. Top with second sheet and brush again. Dip chicken breasts in mixed ingredients, turning to coat thoroughly. Place chicken diagonally on one corner of pastry sheets. Then roll while folding in sides to make a neat rectangular package. Brush top of wrapped chicken with butter and top lightly with Parmesan cheese.

title: hominy hot pot
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add ground beef and cook until lightly browned; drain.
Add salt and pepper, chili powder, sugar and tomatoes.
Stir and allow to simmer 10 minutes. Add hominy; simmer 30 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese spread
directions: Combine wine and cubed cheese in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into small crocks and refrigerate.

title: cantonese beef
directions: Brown beef in oil in large skillet about 5 minutes.
Combine water, gravy mix, soy sauce and ginger.
Add red pepper, water chestnuts and green onions.
Bring to full boil.
Stir in rice. Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: carrots and zucchini
directions: Combine carrot and onion in a medium saucepan.
Add water to barely cover vegetables.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and salt; continue to simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Drain off liquid.
Drizzle vegetables with margarine and serve hot.
Yields 8 servings.
Serving size:
1/2 cup.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, adding 1 stick softened oleo. Bake in a 17 x 11 x 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for about 15 minutes at 350°. Combine next 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat until marshmallows are melted. Spread over cake. In a saucepan, melt remaining ingredients over low heat.
Spread over coconut layer.
Refrigerate.
Will serve 20 people.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix vegetables lightly.
Add dressing; toss gently. Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients with fruit, dot with 1 tablespoon oleo and place in bottom of casserole.
Prepare batter.

title: ranch oysterettes
directions: Mix together the last 5 ingredients; pour over crackers.
Toss until all crackers are covered.
Place crackers on a cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.
Delicious as a snack or in soup.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, milk, cocoa and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Yields 50 cookies.

title: sweet-n-sour smokies
directions: Slow cook all ingredients on low in crock-pot for about 2 hours.

title: crab meat pie
directions: In mixer, blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, horseradish and onion.
Spread into a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over pie mixture.
Chill for 12 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: saltine cracker brittle
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar.
Separately spread saltine crackers on a foil-covered cookie sheet.
Pour on margarine and sugar.
Put in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and dump on chocolate chips; let melt and spread.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: wedding punch
directions: Melt the sugar in water and while still hot, add 1 large package cherry jello (if prefer a green punch, use lime).
Stir until completely dissolved.
Then add the remaining ingredients. Put a small jar of maraschino cherries in a ring mold and freeze with a small amount of punch.
When this is frozen, add more punch to make a larger punch ring.

title: hot squash dip
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender.
Drain well.
Add soup and cheese.
Add drained, chopped pimiento and pepper.
Serve hot.
Tostados are good for dipping.

title: oreo-turtle dessert
directions: Drizzle the caramel sauce and sprinkle the chopped pecans between the layers of cookies and Cool Whip.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening until soft.
Gradually beat in the sugars. Beat in egg and blend thoroughly.
Sift together salt, baking soda and flour (reserving a little flour to sprinkle over the gumdrops) and stir into the first mixture with vanilla.
Add nuts and gumdrop pieces.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix mushroom soup, celery soup and rice together and put into the bottom of baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Place chicken pieces on top and sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Seal with foil and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 325°, then don't peek!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and onion together until broccoli gets done. Drain well. Add cheese, mayonnaise, cream of mushroom soup and well beaten eggs. Mix well and place in 9 x 13 baking dish. Add cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix sugar, oil, and vanilla. Add eggs and pumpkin. Stir in flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, baking powder, allspice, nutmeg and cloves. Pour mixture into ungreased pan. Bake 30 to 45 minutes until done. May be prepared ahead. May be frozen. Yields 2 loaves or 1 10 x 15 pan.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Mix soup, 3/4 cup margarine (melted), chicken, celery, onion and lemon juice and cover rice.
Brown almonds in 1 stick of margarine and place on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Beat eggs well; add to flour mixture.
Blend together until it becomes very thick.
Roll out very thin onto waxed paper that has been well floured.
Cut into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Stack strips (well floured); cut 1/4-inch wide.
Drop into boiling water, a few at a time, and stir.
Cook until tender.
Add Meat Sauce.

title: pork with fennel(healthy choice; serves 6)
directions: Trim fat from pork; coat larger skillet with cooking spray. Add margarine.
Place over medium heat until margarine melts.
Add pork, cook 5 to 6 minutes, turning to brown meat evenly.
Remove pork from skillet.
Add 1/2 cup water, wine, bouillon, fennel seed and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add pork again.
Simmer 5 minutes until pork is tender.
Put pork on platter; keep warm.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1 tablespoon water.
Add to pan.
Stir until thickened.
Pour over pork.
Garnish with fennel sprigs, if desired.
Contains 134 calories per serving, 4.3 grams of fat.

title: nutty green salad
directions: 1. Combine pineapple and pudding and mix until thickened. 2. Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Serves 8.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream softened margarine and sugars. Add additional ingredients in the order listed. Scoop with cookie or melon ball scoop and roll into balls (size of a small walnut). Combine additional 1 cup of granulated sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon. Roll balls of dough in sugar/cinnamon mixture and flatten with the bottom of a glass. Bake 10-12 minutes at 350.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Wash and drain cranberries.
In a pot, combine cranberries and water. Boil for 20 minutes.
Press through a sieve.
Stir in sugar. Cook for 2 minutes over medium heat.
Pour into a jar with a tight fitting lid. Chill.
Yields 4 cups.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Pour rice into the bottom of a baking dish. Set aside 1 tablespoon of onion soup mix.
Spread the remaining onion soup mix over the rice.
Cover with mushrooms, reserving juice.
Add enough hot water to the mushroom juice to make 3 cups. Put pork chops on top and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.

title: new york style cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Crush cookies and melt butter.
Add butter to cookies.
Mix well.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of pan.
Bake 8 minutes.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken and pepper in plastic bag.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into bag and fasten securely. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight, as desired, turning occasionally.
Pour contents of bag into 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender, occasionally spooning sauce over chicken.
Serve with rice, if desired, and additional picante sauce.
Yields 4 servings.

title: steamed salmon
directions: Combine all ingredients in skillet except salmon.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add salmon fillets and cook on medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily.
Remove to a serving platter.
Drain vegetables and place on top of fillets.

title: chocolate cherries
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until caramels are completely melted.
Remove form heat.
Combine cake mix, remaining 1/3 cup milk and butter.
Stir in nuts.
Press 1/2
mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crust.
Pour caramel mixture over chips, spreading evenly.
Crumble remaining cake mixture over caramel mixture.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 18 minutes. Cool.
Chill 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: cornbread(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put the butter in a 2 1/2-quart baking-serving dish or heavy iron skillet and place it in the oven until the butter has melted.
Keep it warm, but don't let the butter burn.
Mix the dry ingredients together, add the milk and beaten eggs, and beat well.
Pour the batter into the hot, buttered pan and bake for 10 minutes.
Then pour the whipping cream into the center of the cornbread
without stirring it and return it to the oven to bake another 20 minutes.
The circumference will be like cornbread, but the center will be almost liquid.

title: curry-cajun spiced chicken
directions: In a 3-quart rectangular baking dish, combine honey, water, mustard, melted margarine, Cajun seasoning, curry powder, lemon juice and garlic; mix well.
Add chicken breast halves, turning to coat.
Arrange in a single layer.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Serve chicken and pan drippings with hot cooked rice.

title: farmers pork chops
directions: Roll pork chops in flour and brown in cooking oil, then add garlic, salt, pepper and onions to oil.
Place potatoes in casserole dish.
Add the browned pork chops on top of the potatoes.
Arrange garlic and onions on top of pork chops.
Blend sour cream with dry mustard.
Pour this over the top of onions. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, 30 minutes.

title: mamaw's potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in just enough water to keep them from burning. While potatoes are cooking, fry bacon until crisp.
Brown onion in 1 tablespoon of bacon drippings.
The onion has a better flavor if it is browned well.

title: gram schrauder's snowballs
directions: Put 4 or 5 cookies together with whipped cream in between. Cover top with whipped cream and cover with coconut.
