Better if set overnight in covered container.
Serves 12.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put alternate layers of drained beans and onions in dish.
Mix soup, milk and basil, then pour this over the layers of beans and onions.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Arrange 1-inch pieces of bacon on top of cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: meringue that won't "weep"
directions: Mix the ingredients and cook until clear.
Set aside.
Beat 3 egg whites until foamy and beginning to peak.
Add cooled cornstarch mixture.
Continue beating until creamy, gradually adding 6 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until very creamy.
Pile on pie and bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: buttercream icing(decorator's icing)
directions: Beat Crisco until fluffy. Add flavoring. Gradually add powdered sugar and milk. (May thin icing more if too stiff by adding milk 1/4 teaspoon at the time. If using liquid food coloring, color icing before thinning.)

title: fat-free fruit cup
directions: Mix all fruits from can and their juice.
Cut up apple and banana.
Mix together.
Sprinkle Jell-O pudding mix straight from box.
Stir slightly.
Pour into dishes.
Chill and serve.

title: banana squares
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add banana and mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli with cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender.
Drain and place in greased casserole dish.
Make a sauce with the butter, flour, salt, milk, pepper and cheese.
Sprinkle nuts over broccoli, then pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbling hot and browned on top.
Yields 8 servings.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clam liquid into a small skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Add chopped clams and heat below boiling point for 2 or 3 minutes. Drain and put into a food processor with steel blade.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend remaining ingredients except shrimp; cook slowly for 30 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Stir in shrimp and cook until pink.
Serve over hot, cooked rice and enjoy.

title: turnip greens with cornmeal dumplings
directions: Cut off and discard tough stems and discolored leaves from turnip greens.
Wash greens thoroughly and place in a Dutch oven. Add salt and enough cold water to cover.
Let soak 1 hour.
Rinse and drain.
Combine 4 cups water and salt pork in Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Add greens; return to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender.

title: cheesy fiesta casserole
directions: Saute sausage, mushrooms and onion in a large skillet until sausage is completely cooked.
Drain well; set aside.
Combine eggs and sour cream in a blender; season with salt and pepper. Whip eggs for 1 minute.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° until eggs are softly set, 5 to 8 minutes. Spoon salsa evenly over the top of eggs, then spread sausage mixture over the top.
Top with combined cheeses.
Cover; refrigerate until 30 minutes before serving time.
Bake at 325° until cheeses are melted, about 30 minutes.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Pour into three 8 or 9-inch pans.
Line pans with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost cake with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: cheese drop biscuits
directions: Mix cheese, shortening and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, blending thoroughly.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Biscuits should be the size of small walnuts.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown in a 425° oven.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix, press in greased pan for 15 minutes at 350 degrees. Cool.

title: jack daniel's glazed ham
directions: Place ham on rack in roasting pan.
Do not add water.
Roast at 325° uncovered for 20 minutes per pound or until meat thermometer reads 140°.
Before ham is thoroughly cooked, simmer a mixture of the remaining 5 ingredients over medium-low heat for 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.
About 20 minutes before ham is ready, brush glaze over ham.
Serve garnished with orange slices and endive leaves.
Serves 6.
tags: fully cooked boneless smoked ham half

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix with 4 ounces of milk and butter.
Pour 1/2 mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes. Unwrap caramels and add 1/3 cup milk.
Melt over heat while cake cools.
Pour caramel mixture over cake.
Put nuts and chocolate chips on top.
Dot remaining cake batter on top.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Let set 24 hours before cutting into squares.

title: western hash
directions: Brown beef.
Add all ingredients, except cheese.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.
Heat until melted.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chocolate chips, butter and corn syrup in saucepan. Stir over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix lightly until well coated.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Keep refrigerated.

title: heart healthy almond pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Mix ingredients in a large bowl and beat for three minutes at medium to high speed of electric mixer. Pour batter into a 10 inch nonstick-coated Bundt pan and bake until cake is springy and lightly brown, about 60 to 70 minutes. Then invert pan and turn out cake.
Let cool completely on a rack.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix water and soup.
Add onion, celery and Accent.
Add tuna. Add noodles and cashews just before baking.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat in xxx sugar.
Add peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and blend well. Pour into crust and freeze.
Take out 1/2 hour before serving. Garnish with chocolate syrup or Cool Whip.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Slice rolls lengthwise (like a layer cake). Spread both sides with mixture. Put sliced ham on bottom half. Put cheese on top of ham. Put top half back on. Put back in foil pan. Wrap in foil. At this point, they can be frozen for up to 3 weeks. Defrost or if not frozen, heat at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese has melted slightly and middle is hot.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix together eggs (beaten), pudding and milk.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Pour liquid mixture into dry ingredients.
Stir in melted butter, 3 tablespoons.
Pour mixture into a shallow greased pan to depth of about 2-inches.

title: barbecue jack pots
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Simmer while preparing muffin tins.
Press biscuits around sides and bottom of tins to form cups.
Fill each 3/4 full of mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of each cup.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are brown.

title: sweet-sour carrots
directions: Brown butter; blend in cornstarch and continue browning, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings.
Combine sugar, vinegar and water and add to the first mixture gradually.
Cook slowly until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over hot carrots.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs, sugar and sour cream. Stir in vanilla. Mix dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture. Roll out or drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix salmon, onion and lemon juice with fork.
Add beaten egg to salmon mix.
Add enough flour to hold mixture together. Make patties and cook on medium heat until golden brown.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Use 3-quart casserole.
Cut potatoes like French fries.
Layer part of potatoes in bottom of dish.
Add salt and pepper and 4 to 5 slices of Old English cheese.
Repeat another layer of potatoes and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Pour on 1/2 pint whipping cream. Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients gently and shape into 1-inch balls. Put raw vegetables on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown; turn once.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Place half of mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Chunk up chicken and place on top of stuffing.
Blend soups and broth together.
Pour over chicken and add remaining stuffing over top.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: microwave mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in microwave dish until beef is no longer red and onion is transparent.
Stir to break up meat; drain.
Stir in soup and chopped green chilies.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into a clean, dry, glass container with a tight-fitting cover. Refrigerate for up to 1 month.

title: egg custard
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dash top with nutmeg.
Bake in a very hot oven at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 minutes or until set.

title: meat loaf
directions: Dice red onion.
In medium bowl, blend all ingredients together.
Fingers are the best mixers for this.
Shape into a loaf and bake in loaf pan for 45 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, butter, powdered sugar and press into 8 x 8 inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk and egg; stir in onions.
Shape dough into balls.
Drop in deep fat and fry until brown.

title: ribbon jello
directions: Odd numbered layers:
Dissolve gelatin in 3/4 cup of boiling water; add 3/4 cup of cold water.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, butter, powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon grated lemon peel.
Press into 8 x 8 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Build 1/2 edge.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix remaining dry ingredients; grate both lemon peels.
Juice both lemons and remove seeds.
Add with grating to dry ingredients. Beat 3 minutes or until fluffy.
Pour over crust.

title: bacon quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese and bacon in pie shell.
Beat remaining ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm and browned.

title: easy chicken a la king
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring often.
Serve over chow mein noodles, rice or toasted bread.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: party ryes
directions: Mix cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Spread on slices of party rye.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: quick layer cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Break 8 graham cracker squares.
Pour butter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with graham cracker crumbs pressing evenly in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over crumbs.
Layer in order listed all remaining ingredients, pouring milk over entire mixture.
Bake 25 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: beef and potato skillet
directions: I like fried potatoes fixed this way better than whole potatoes.

title: orange dessert
directions: Mix puddings, jello and water.
Cook 10 minutes after it starts to boil.
Let cool; add Cool Whip and oranges.
Place in refrigerator.

title: cool easy jello cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions and let cool.
Prepare jello as directed.
When cake is cool, poke several holes with a knife.
Pour liquid jello over cake and refrigerate several hours. Spread Cool Whip over cake just before serving, OR whip cream until peaks form; add sugar and vanilla, and spread over cake.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Roll potato chips in bag(s) until crushed fine.
Cream butter and sugar very well.
Mix sugar/butter mix with flour, vanilla and potato chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Remove from oven; let cool, then sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and oleo. Add bananas and eggs. Mix well. Add dry ingredients. Bake in loaf or tube pan for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Make a sauce by adding soup, lemon juice and seasonings.
Fold rice and shrimp into sauce.
Then fold in sour cream and pour into one-quart buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: company chicken
directions: Lightly grease and line 9 x 13-inch baking pan with 1/2 of the dried beef slices.
Place chicken breasts over beef slices.
Place remaining beef slices on top of chicken breasts, set aside.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, milk and sour cream and pour over beef and chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 2 hours, then increase temperature to 350° and bake uncovered for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: marinated potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Meanwhile, beat together vinegar, corn oil, sugar, salt and pepper and set aside.
Slice potatoes and put into large bowl.
Add egg, onion and parsley and toss lightly.
Immediately pour oil mixture over potatoes but do not toss.
Let marinate 1 hour.
Add mayonnaise and toss lightly. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Salt and pepper potatoes; set aside.
Brown pork chops in a skillet.
Salt and pepper.
Place chops in bottom of a baking dish, placing potatoes on top of chops.
Dilute soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over chops and potatoes; bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk custards
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in uncooked pie shells.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400° and for 1 hour at 300°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs with fork, then add water and salt.
Add enough flour to make a very stiff dough.
Roll very thin and cut noodles.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: tamale pie casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 2-quart casserole with corn chips.
Add layer of mixture of chili con carne, corn, cheese and olives.
Add another layer of corn chips and repeat layers until ingredients are used.
Pour tomato juice over entire dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Separate beef and place on bottom of glass casserole dish. Wrap bacon around chicken breasts and lay on top of beef slices. Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, covered.
Bake 30 minutes more, uncovered.

title: microwave smoked sausage and peppers
directions: Cook pasta.
Toss with 1/4 cup vinaigrette.
Add tomato and black olives.
Set aside.
Combine olive oil, peppers, asparagus and garlic in a microwave-safe container.
Cover; microwave on High until vegetables are tender, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Place sausage and remaining vinaigrette in another container.
Cover; microwave on High until sausage is hot, about 3 to 6 minutes.
Combine sausage and pepper mixtures; serve over pasta.
Add pepper to taste.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Beat the eggs, salt, pepper, cream and cayenne pepper. Grate cheese on bottom of unbaked pie crust. Pour egg mixture and bacon over cheese. Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cool 5 to 7 minutes.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix well and store in jar in refrigerator.

title: green pea and apple salad
directions: Rinse peas in colander until just thawed.
Drain thoroughly. Combine the peas, apple and onions and toss lightly with Horseradish Cream Dressing.
Chill.
Fry bacon until crisp and drain.
At serving time, garnish the salad with the bacon.

title: chicken crescents
directions: In medium bowl, mix chicken, cream cheese, soup, milk and spices.

title: apricot salad
directions: Cream dry jello with cream cheese. Bring sugar and pineapple to a boil; add to jello mixture and mix well. Add cold water and chill until it begins to set. Stir in Cool Whip and nuts and chill until congealed.

title: ham-it-up snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Place ham slices on rectangles.
Spread ham slices with mustard, sprinkle with cheese.
Starting at shortest side, roll up and seal edges.
Coat rolls with sesame seed.
Cut each roll into 5 slices.
Place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm. Yields 20 appetizer servings.

title: recipe for making friends
directions: Be sure to add a teaspoon of gaiety that sings and then the ability to laugh at little things.
Moisten with a few tears of heart felt sympathy.
Bake in a good natured pan.
Serve repeatedly.

title: chocolate texas sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil the oleo, water and cocoa.
Add the oleo, water and cocoa mixture to the combined mixture and blend well.
Add baking soda, eggs and sour cream; mix well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, no longer.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Heat milk.
Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch with small amount of heated milk.
Stir in egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Add unmelted butter, vanilla, chips to color, coconut and pecans.
Cool shortly. Put into a 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: homemade salami
directions: Break up hamburger.
Mix next 8 ingredients in bowl and pour over meat.
Add water and smoke. Mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: slim salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into 1 1/2-quart container.
Chill until set (3 to 4 hours).
Recommended in summer with barbecued chicken. Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.
Each 1/2 cup serving equals 150 calories or 1 bread and 2 fruit exchanges.

title: frango mint pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add melted chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, vanilla and flavoring.
Pour into pie shell and freeze. Twenty minutes before serving, remove from freezer.
Top with whipped cream and serve.

title: egg yolk sponge cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sift together and set aside the flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat in mixing bowl until very thick and lemon colored the egg yolks.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Blend in slowly on low speed the boiling water and vanilla.
Quickly blend in dry ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake until top springs back at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: venison stew
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Brown stew meat.
Add onions, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Continue cooking until vegetables are tender.

title: quick tortellini soup
directions: Saute garlic cloves lightly in olive oil.
Add chicken or vegetable stock and fresh tortellini.
Cook until tortellini is tender (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Serve immediately, topped with cheese.

title: oatmeal wheat bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In mixing bowl, lightly beat egg.
Stir in milk, oil and brown sugar. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake 30 or 40 minutes or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean. Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Slice squash in 1/2-inch pieces.
Boil three minutes until tender.
Drain; add onion, eggs and seasonings.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 1-quart greased casserole.
Mix butter and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until browned.
During last five minutes of cooking, grate Cheddar cheese on top of casserole to melt.

title: baked fillet(tastes like lobster!)
directions: Cut fillets into serving pieces. Place in greased shallow baking dish or pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice, paprika and a dash of salt and pepper. In saucepan, blend 2 tablespoons of butter with flour and dash each of salt and pepper; add milk all at once. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly; pour over fish. Blend crumbs with remaining butter and sprinkle over fish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Scald milk. Cool to lukewarm; add flour to make a thick batter.
Add yeast and eggs; beat well.
Add flour to make a soft dough; knead until satiny.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Shape into any kind of roll.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 350° to 375°.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bacon and olives.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 12.

title: pink easy salad
directions: Place cottage cheese in a bowl.
Stir in Jell-O.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Mix together.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: reese's cup cake
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients almost to a boil.
Add the sugar, flour and vanilla.
Mix together with the other ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a sheet pan.
When cake comes out of oven, spread on top of cake 1 tablespoon oil and 1 cup peanut butter.

title: best ever no cholesterol pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans by spraying with Pam or greasing with margarine wrapper.

title: chili
directions: Coat the beef cubes with flour and braise in peanut oil.
Cook the beans 1 1/2 hours and drain.
Add all the other ingredients. Simmer until done.

title: wassail bowl
directions: In a large pot or crock-pot, bring cider and all juices to a boil.
Put cloves and cinnamon sticks in a mesh bag and add to cider and juices.
Lower heat.
Add honey and nutmeg.
Cover and simmer for thirty minutes or until ready to serve.
Garnish with clove-studded orange slices floating on top.
Serve pretty warm with an individual cinnamon stick.
Serves 25.

title: gooey butter bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and oleo in bowl.
Pat firmly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and eggs with blender; pour over cake mix.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes(yummy)
directions: Lay potato on cutting board, using handle of wooden spoon as stopper, slice potato almost through, thin.
Place potatoes in baking dish, fan slightly to open slices, and salt and pepper. Sprinkle with herbs such as parsley, thyme, chives or dill (we like chives and dill).
Drizzle with butter or margarine.

title: school bell cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Add Karo syrup. Mix flour, salt, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg together; add to creamed mixture.
Add soda in hot water.
Add last the chopped dates and some chopped nutmeats.
Chill.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Frost when cool.

title: chocolate passion dessert
directions: Layer cookies in bottom of a serving bowl, then spread with 1 cup strawberries.
Slice and layer 1 banana and 1 cup pudding. Repeat layers, ending with pudding.
Garnish with strawberries. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: shrimp sherry
directions: Saute
vegetables
and	shrimp in butter, individually. Set aside
in warm oven.
To chicken broth made from bouillon cubes, add
some
cornstarch
and a couple of good "glugs" of sherry. Cook
until
thickened.
Put all ingredients together and
add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice.
(Amounts are strictly determined by number of people to be served.)

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in a large pot.
Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop cookies onto wax paper.
Let cool about 20 minutes.

title: kashiwa mochi
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Divide the dough into 32 pieces and fill with an (sweet bean filling).
Use slightly oiled banana leaves or ti leaves to wrap the dough.
Steam for 2 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp and drain.
Save 2 to 3 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble the bacon.
Saute onion in drippings.
Blend in flour slowly.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens slightly.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: hot corn
directions: Combine eggs, corn, corn meal, oil, garlic salt and baking soda in large bowl.
Pour half of mix into a casserole.
Top with chilies and half of cheese.
Cover with remaining mixture and top with the balance of cheese.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: great grits
directions: In a medium saucepan, simmer first four ingredients until onion is just soft.
Add grits and salt; bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat, stirring occasionally, until grits reach desired thickness.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted. Serve hot.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and lemon extract.
Pour into condensed milk and stir thoroughly.
Add egg yolks and blend well.
Pour mixture into crust.
Add meringue.
Brown on 325°.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: green tomato crisp
directions: Mix lime and water.
Add sliced tomatoes and soak for 24 hours.
Drain and soak for 4 hours in fresh water, changing water every hour.
Drain again.
Make syrup of sugar, vinegar and spices.
Bring to boil.
Pour over tomatoes and let stand overnight.
In morning, boil 1 hour.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: layer overnight salad
directions: In a large bowl place ingredients in layers as given.
Cover bowl air tight and put in refrigerator overnight or for several hours.
Toss just before serving.
Use 1/4 recipe to serve 4.

title: great grandma's banana bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar, adding sugar gradually. Blend in the bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted mixture to the creamed butter/sugar combination alternately with the buttermilk until all is well blended.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: make ahead breakfast
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Tear up bread and place in dish.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.

title: parker house rolls(from the files of dessie bell hayes)
directions: Add sugar to milk; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until smooth.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Pour mixture into large bowl and add flour (1/2 cup at a time), 1/4 cup sugar, shortening and salt.
Mix well, then put on floured board.
Knead until dough is smooth.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Knead and work again.
Make into rolls. Put in greased muffin tins and let rise again.
Cook at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
These rolls can be made in 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let stand until soft, then mix well.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Top with a cherry.
Refrigerate.
May be frozen.

title: turkey tetrazzini(microwave)
directions: Mix drained spaghetti, mushrooms, olives and pimento.
Blend cream of mushroom soup with chicken broth and microwave on Medium heat for approximately 5 minutes.
Add cooking sherry and cheese to sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix sauce with spaghetti mixture and turkey.

title: acorn squash
directions: Prick squash several times.
Microwave on High, about 11 to 13 minutes, until soft when pricked with a fork.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Cut in half and remove seeds.
Place cut side up in a 10-inch square casserole.
Set aside.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken and cool.	Cut into bite-sized pieces and layer in long casserole dish.
Heat soups, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
In a saucepan melt margarine and stuffing mix and broth.
Spread on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon-dill chicken
directions: Whisk together first 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken in bowl suitable for marinating.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours, but no longer than 24 hours.
Grill over medium-hot coals, brushing chicken with marinade to keep moist.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients, using a spoon.
Eat immediately.

title: fluffy banana pudding
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Combine all ingredients.
Pack in mixing bowl lined with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight. Turn out.
Ice with Cool Whip and coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheesy chicken mac bake
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, in hot margarine, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper until smooth.
Add macaroni, cheese (reserve 1/4 cup cheese) and chicken.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with reserved cheese; bake until cheese melts.

title: popeye biscuits
directions: Brush tops with melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Brush tops again.

title: great grandma's cookies
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, milk, salt and vanilla together.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Mix mixtures together; add butter or shortening and mix together.
Chill dough and roll out.
Bake at 325°.
Don't let cookies get too dark or they get hard.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Sprinkle salt, oregano and pepper over meat.
Add bread crumbs and evaporated milk; mix well.
Pat mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: steak marinated
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate overnight.
Then grill.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Wash
beans
and
soak overnight.
Chop onion and green pepper in small pieces and saute in bacon grease.
Bring beans to boil and add all other ingredients; let simmer for several hours.
When just about done, add salt and pepper.
When done mash through several
times
with
potato
masher
to thicken juice.
If too thick,
add
a little hot water.
Cook about 2 cups of rice
for listed amount.
Chop white onion to put over top.

title: ohio ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine bread crumbs and onion.
Stir in eggs and milk.
Add ham, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pat into a large loaf pan.
Press brown sugar on top. Cover with foil and bake for 2 hours.
After 1 hour remove foil and baste top of loaf with melted brown sugar.
Replace foil. After 90 minutes remove foil and baste again.
Cook uncovered the remaining 30 minutes.
Serve directly from pan.

title: hershey cake
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix with Hershey's mixture.
Sift flour and add slowly with buttermilk which soda has been added.
Mix well and add vanilla.
Cook 1 hour in tube pan at 350°.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and chill until congealed.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil frozen vegetables for 2 minutes in salted water; drain and cool.
Mix package of salad dressing with oil and vinegar.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, olives, celery, green pepper and green onions.
Add to cooled, boiled vegetables.
Add salad dressing mixture.
Toss.
Let stand for 12 to 24 hours (refrigerated), stirring a couple of times.

title: clam chowder
directions: Place clams and juice in pan.
Add potatoes and onions.
Salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add soup and butter.
Return to heat; stir until soup is smooth.
Add milk to desired consistency.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil water and sugar, empty frozen juice into sugar water, mix well and cool. Add the rest of the ingredients, stir well and pour into container and freeze.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Brown onion in shortening.
Add paprika, pepper, salt and chicken.
Brown chicken 10 minutes.
Add water and simmer until tender (45 to 60 minutes).
Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to liquid and mix well.
Add dumplings; arrange chicken on top and heat well.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook ingredients, except egg whites, until it forms a ball. Pour half in egg whites.
Cook the rest about 1 minute.
Pour in egg whites.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with sugar and melted margarine.
Mix well and press in two 8-inch pie plates.
Put in oven for 6 minutes at 300°.
Take out and set aside.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture to large bowl.
Stir in oats and butterscotch morsels.
Drop by level measuring tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix good and bake 1 hour at 350°.
This is a family recipe.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Use a double boiler.
Melt chocolate squares.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk.
Cook until thick.
Add hot water, salt and sugar, cook until smooth.
This is wonderful on vanilla ice cream.
Top with nuts and whip cream.

title: granola crunch
directions: Combine honey, peanut butter, oil and brown sugar in a saucepan; heat until it comes to a simmer.
Preheat oven to 300°. Combine all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon mixture into rectangular pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.
Makes 12 cups.

title: mccall's microwave sweet-and-sour chicken
directions: In large, shallow microwave-safe dish, toss chicken with sherry, 2 teaspoons soy sauce and the ground ginger.
Remove and discard stem, rib and seeds from peppers.
Cut peppers into strips. Cut strips in half crosswise; set aside.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together and put into jello mold or dish and put into refrigerator until congealed.

title: roast pork
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix flour and apple juice in baking dish.
Place roast and liquid in a 10 x 16-inch cooking bag.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Close bag.
Make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top of bag and bake in baking dish for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush wafers and mix thoroughly with coconut, pecans and raisins.
Add milk and mix with hands.
Place in a loaf pan lined with wax paper, pressing together firmly.
Place in refrigerator with a heavy weight on top overnight.
Then slice as needed; store in refrigerator when not in use.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Place beef in a 3-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt, basil and pepper.
Top with celery, carrots, potatoes, onions and peas.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over meat and vegetables, coating all pieces. Cover tightly and bake at 300° for 3 hours. Makes its own gravy.
This recipe can be doubled or tripled for a larger amount.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Pour filling into a greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 5 - 7 minutes or until heated. Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, cream butter, cream cheese and vanilla. Place cake mix in another bowl; cut in cream cheese mixture until crumbly. Sprinkle over hot filling. Bake 25 - 30 minutes longer or until topping is golden brown.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Spray pizza pan lightly with nonstick cooking spray and wipe off excess.
Roll out dough and place on pan.
Let rise.
Add sauce and other toppings.
Put on bottom rack in a cold oven. Turn oven to 500°.
Bake 17 to 20 minutes, depending on oven.

title: irresistible low-fat chocolate brownies(makes 18 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a 2-quart glass measure with handle, combine condensed milk, cocoa and chocolate chips.
Cook in microwave oven on 100% power 2 minutes or until chips are melted, stirring after each minute. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: 24 hour egg omelet
directions: Butter one side of bread.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Place bread evenly in well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and sausage.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper. Pour over bread mix.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake, covered, in oven at 325° for about 1 hour, or until mix is set. Uncover last 5 minutes of baking.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tatum's ham and cheese
directions: Saute onion in butter and mustard slowly until tender.
Split the pan of rolls together, taking off the top layer.
Pour butter and onion mixture over the bottom.
Place ham on top of this and grated cheese on top of ham.
Replace tops of rolls and wrap in foil.
Bake in 325° oven for about 30 minutes.
Take off foil and brush tops with butter.
Brown lightly.
(Leave the rolls in the pans that they come in even when ready to serve.)

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Add onion when half done.
Cook until browned; drain.
Combine sugar, catsup and pork and beans in slow cooker.
Mix well.
Stir in ground beef mixture.
Cook on high for 2 hours.

title: south of the border chip dip
directions: Cut up Velveeta cheese into small squares and place in crock-pot on high.
Add milk.
While cheese is melting, brown, then drain meat.
Add meat and sauces to crock-pot, turn to low setting.
When cheese is melted completely, serve with chips.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift salt, baking powder and flour.
Add to creamed mixture, then add vanilla and 1 cup of coconut.
Using teaspoon, make ball and roll in coconut. Bake at 350°.

title: never-fail dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl. Beat egg in a measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Add to dry ingredients, beating until all the flour is mixed in.
Let raise 5 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot beef stew or chicken broth. Cook for 20 minutes, covered.

title: prairie fire
directions: Drain beans, reserving 2/3 cup liquid; mash.
In saucepan, combine beans, reserved liquid, butter, cheese, pepper, onion, garlic and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Heat and stir until hot. Transfer to chafing dish; place over hot water. Serve with chips.
Makes 6 cups; can be halved.

title: diana's apple pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs, margarine, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add chopped apples.
Pour in a deep dish pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Lower heat to 400° and finish baking.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain fat.
Spray a casserole dish with Pam. Spread and seal rolls in bottom of pan.
Add sausage.
Beat eggs and add cheese and milk. Pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast in water with onion, celery, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Debone and reserve liquid.
Mix soups with tomatoes.
Butter casserole.
Line dish with Doritos that have been crushed.
Next add a layer of chicken, then soup mixture, then cheese.
Repeat.
Pour 1 can of reserved broth over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
If desired, jalapeno peppers may be added to soup mixture.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown pork chops on each side and add onion.
Put in roaster.
Add potatoes that have been peeled and sliced.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over pork chops, onion and potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Add a little milk if it thickens too much.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Grease bottom of oblong casserole dish.
Place 1/2 package of stuffing mix in bottom of dish.
Make boned chicken your next layer.
Mix together soups and milk and pour over chicken.
Slice boiled eggs over this, then layer chopped onions.
Sprinkle with the rest of the stuffing.
Pour chicken broth over all and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: stir-fried shrimp with broccoli
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over high heat.
Add green onions, ginger and garlic.
Stir-fry about 1 minute.
Add shrimp and stir-fry until shrimp turn pink, about 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and stir-fry about 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl; mix well.
Pour over shrimp-broccoli mixture.
Cook and stir until sauce boils and thickens, about 2 minutes more.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well, with the exception of nuts.
Add those last.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Add all ingredients into casserole dish.
Put chicken on top, push down a little.
Leave out 1 cup of all 3 cans of soup. Pour over chicken.
Cook until chicken is tender.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill for several hours or overnight. Serve with assorted raw vegetables cut into bite size pieces.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan. Combine next 6 ingredients in large plastic bag; set aside. Place half potatoes in bag;
shake well to coat. Place in single layer in baking pan. Repeat with remaining potatoes. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a 2 quart saucepan stir together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Stir in slightly beaten egg yolks.
Bring to a boil over medium heat stirring constantly to prevent sticking.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Cool slightly and stir in 3/4 cup coconut. Spoon filling into cooled pastry shell.
